  26# The db_model can be a bit tricky as SQL is represented a few ways depending
  27# on how close to a final result we are.
  28# The end representation is a single string.
  29# The nearly there representation is a list of strings, which makes indenting much easier.
  30# The primary computational representation is a NearSQL structure, as it is a dag of objects.
  31# Note: near sql has a bound/unbound variation treating the top layer differently than
  32# subordinate nodes.
  33
  34
  35def _list_join_expecting_list(joiner: str, str_list: List[str]) -> List[str]:
  36    assert isinstance(joiner, str)
  37    assert isinstance(str_list, list)
  38    assert all([isinstance(vi, str) for vi in str_list])
  39    n = len(str_list)
  40    return [" " + str_list[i] + (joiner if i < (n - 1) else "") for i in range(n)]

  43def _clean_annotation(annotation: Optional[str]) -> Optional[str]:
  44    assert isinstance(annotation, (str, type(None)))
  45    if annotation is None:
  46        return annotation
  47    annotation = annotation.strip()
  48    annotation = re.sub(r"(\s|\r|\n)+", " ", annotation)
  49    annotation = annotation.replace(
  50        "%", "percent"
  51    )  # SQL alchemy doesn't like these in comments
  52    return annotation.strip()

  58def _db_lag_expr(dbmodel, expression):
  59    arg_0 = dbmodel.expr_to_sql(expression.args[0], want_inline_parens=False)
  60    if len(expression.args) == 1:
  61        return f"LAG({arg_0})"
  62    elif len(expression.args) == 2:
  63        periods = expression.args[1].value
  64        if periods > 0:
  65            return f"LAG({arg_0}, {periods})"
  66        elif periods < 0:
  67            return f"LEAD({arg_0}, {-periods})"
  68        else:
  69            raise ValueError("shift by zero not supported")
  70    else:
  71        raise ValueError("too many arguments to SQL LAG/LEAD")

  74# Note, mod should not always equal remainder:
  75# https://rob.conery.io/2018/08/21/mod-and-remainder-are-not-the-same/
  76# But they do in numpy, which we will use as the
  77# reference implementation.
  78# import numpy as np
  79# np.mod([5, 5, -5, 5], [2, -2, 2, -2])
  80# # array([ 1, -1,  1, -1])
  81# np.remainder([5, 5, -5, 5], [2, -2, 2, -2])
  82# # array([ 1, -1,  1, -1])
  83# so we are just going to send it out and use destination semantics
  84def _db_mod_expr(dbmodel, expression):
  85    return (
  86        "MOD("
  87        + dbmodel.expr_to_sql(expression.args[0], want_inline_parens=False)
  88        + ", "
  89        + dbmodel.expr_to_sql(expression.args[1], want_inline_parens=False)
  90        + ")"
  91    )
  92
  93
  94# extend to floating point
  95# import numpy as np
  96# e0 = np.array([5, 5, -5, -5])
  97# e1 = np.array([2, -2, 2, -2])
  98# (e0 - np.floor(e0 / (1.0 * e1)) * e1)
  99# # array([ 1., -1.,  1., -1.])
 100def _db_remainder_expr(dbmodel, expression):
 101    e0 = dbmodel.expr_to_sql(expression.args[0], want_inline_parens=True)
 102    e1 = dbmodel.expr_to_sql(expression.args[1], want_inline_parens=True)
 103    return f"({e0} - FLOOR({e0} / (1.0 * {e1})) * {e1})"

 117def _db_is_null_expr(dbmodel, expression):

 125def _db_is_inf_expr(dbmodel, expression):
 126    subexpr = dbmodel.expr_to_sql(expression.args[0], want_inline_parens=True)
 127    plus_inf = f"CAST({dbmodel.value_to_sql('+infinity')} AS {dbmodel.float_type})"
 128    minus_inf = f"CAST({dbmodel.value_to_sql('-infinity')} AS {dbmodel.float_type})"
 129    return (
 130        "(CASE"
 131        + f" WHEN {subexpr} IS NULL THEN FALSE"
 132        + f" WHEN NOT (({subexpr} > {minus_inf}) AND ({subexpr} < {plus_inf})) THEN TRUE"
 133        + " ELSE FALSE"
 134        + " END)"
 135    )
 136
 137
 138def _db_is_nan_expr(dbmodel, expression):
 139    subexpr = dbmodel.expr_to_sql(expression.args[0], want_inline_parens=True)
 140    return (
 141        "(CASE"
 142        + f" WHEN {subexpr} IS NULL THEN TRUE"
 143        + f" WHEN ({subexpr} > 0) AND (-{subexpr} > 0) THEN TRUE"
 144        + f" WHEN ({subexpr} != {subexpr}) THEN TRUE"
 145        + f" WHEN ({subexpr} != 0) AND ({subexpr} = -{subexpr}) THEN TRUE"
 146        + " ELSE FALSE"
 147        + " END)"
 148    )

 151def _db_is_bad_expr(dbmodel, expression):
 152    subexpr = dbmodel.expr_to_sql(expression.args[0], want_inline_parens=True)
 153    plus_inf = f"CAST({dbmodel.value_to_sql('+infinity')} AS {dbmodel.float_type})"
 154    minus_inf = f"CAST({dbmodel.value_to_sql('-infinity')} AS {dbmodel.float_type})"
 155    return (
 156        "(CASE"
 157        + f" WHEN {subexpr} IS NULL THEN TRUE"
 158        + f" WHEN ({subexpr} > 0) AND (-{subexpr} > 0) THEN TRUE"
 159        + f" WHEN ({subexpr} != {subexpr}) THEN TRUE"
 160        + f" WHEN ({subexpr} != 0) AND ({subexpr} = -{subexpr}) THEN TRUE"
 161        + f" WHEN NOT (({subexpr} > {minus_inf}) AND ({subexpr} < {plus_inf})) THEN TRUE"
 162        + " ELSE FALSE"
 163        + " END)"
 164    )

 167def _db_if_else_expr(dbmodel, expression):
 168    assert len(expression.args) == 3
 169    if_expr = dbmodel.expr_to_sql(expression.args[0], want_inline_parens=True)
 170    x_expr = dbmodel.expr_to_sql(expression.args[1], want_inline_parens=True)
 171    y_expr = dbmodel.expr_to_sql(expression.args[2], want_inline_parens=True)
 172    return (
 173        "CASE"
 174        + " WHEN "
 175        + if_expr
 176        + " THEN "
 177        + x_expr
 178        + " WHEN NOT "
 179        + if_expr
 180        + " THEN "
 181        + y_expr
 182        + " ELSE "
 183        + "NULL"
 184        + " END"
 185    )

 188def _db_where_expr(dbmodel, expression):
 189    assert len(expression.args) == 3
 190    if_expr = dbmodel.expr_to_sql(expression.args[0], want_inline_parens=True)
 191    x_expr = dbmodel.expr_to_sql(expression.args[1], want_inline_parens=True)
 192    y_expr = dbmodel.expr_to_sql(expression.args[2], want_inline_parens=True)
 193    return "CASE" + " WHEN " + if_expr + " THEN " + x_expr + " ELSE " + y_expr + " END"

 196def _db_mapv(dbmodel, expression):
 197    if_expr = dbmodel.expr_to_sql(expression.args[0], want_inline_parens=True)
 198    mapping_dict = expression.args[1]
 199    default_value_expr = dbmodel.expr_to_sql(
 200        expression.args[2], want_inline_parens=True
 201    )
 202    terms = [
 203        "WHEN " + dbmodel.value_to_sql(k) + " THEN " + dbmodel.value_to_sql(v)
 204        for k, v in mapping_dict.value.items()
 205    ]
 206    if len(terms) <= 0:
 207        return default_value_expr
 208    return (
 209        "CASE"
 210        + " "
 211        + if_expr
 212        + " "
 213        + " ".join(terms)
 214        + " ELSE "
 215        + default_value_expr
 216        + " END"
 217    )

 338def _db_count_expr(dbmodel, expression):
 339    """Count number of non-null entries (as in Pandas)"""
 340    if len(expression.args) != 1:
 341        return "SUM(1)"
 342    e0 = dbmodel.expr_to_sql(expression.args[0], want_inline_parens=True)
 343    return f"SUM(CASE WHEN {e0} IS NOT NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)"

 359def _db_pow_expr(dbmodel, expression):
 360    if isinstance(expression.args[1], data_algebra.expr_rep.Value) and (
 361        expression.args[1].value == 1
 362    ):
 363        return dbmodel.expr_to_sql(expression.args[0], want_inline_parens=True)
 364    return (
 365        "POWER("
 366        + dbmodel.expr_to_sql(expression.args[0], want_inline_parens=False)
 367        + ", "
 368        + dbmodel.expr_to_sql(expression.args[1], want_inline_parens=False)
 369        + ")"
 370    )

 381def _db_around_expr(dbmodel, expression):
 382    if isinstance(expression.args[1], data_algebra.expr_rep.Value) and (
 383        expression.args[1].value == 0
 384    ):
 385        return dbmodel.expr_to_sql(expression.args[0].round(), want_inline_parens=False)
 386    mult = data_algebra.expr_rep.Value(10.0).__pow__(expression.args[1])
 387    derived = (expression.args[0] * mult).round() / mult
 388    return dbmodel.expr_to_sql(derived, want_inline_parens=True)

 413def _db_float_divide_expr(dbmodel, expression):
 414    # don't issue an error
 415    # https://cloud.google.com/bigquery/docs/reference/standard-sql/mathematical_functions#ieee_divide
 416    assert len(expression.args) == 2
 417    e0 = dbmodel.expr_to_sql(expression.args[0], want_inline_parens=True)
 418    e1 = dbmodel.expr_to_sql(expression.args[1], want_inline_parens=True)
 419    return f"({e0} / (1.0 * {e1}))"

 695def _annotated_method_catalogue(
 696    model_name: str,
 697) -> Tuple[
 698    Set[data_algebra.data_ops_types.MethodUse],
 699    Set[data_algebra.data_ops_types.MethodUse],
 700]:
 701    """
 702    Prepare method lookup tables
 703
 704    :param: model name (used as column key)
 705    :return: (known_method_uses, recommended_method_uses)
 706    """
 707    known_method_uses: Set[data_algebra.data_ops_types.MethodUse] = set()
 708    recommended_method_uses: Set[data_algebra.data_ops_types.MethodUse] = set()
 709    for i in range(data_algebra.op_catalog.methods_table.shape[0]):
 710        row = data_algebra.op_catalog.methods_table.loc[i, :]
 711        matches = []
 712        if row["op_class"] in {"p", "up"}:
 713            matches.append(
 714                data_algebra.data_ops_types.MethodUse(
 715                    row["op"],
 716                    is_project=True,
 717                    is_windowed=False,
 718                    is_ordered=False,
 719                )
 720            )
 721        elif row["op_class"] == "g":
 722            matches.append(
 723                data_algebra.data_ops_types.MethodUse(
 724                    row["op"],
 725                    is_project=False,
 726                    is_windowed=True,
 727                    is_ordered=False,
 728                )
 729            )
 730        elif row["op_class"] == "w":
 731            matches.append(
 732                data_algebra.data_ops_types.MethodUse(
 733                    row["op"],
 734                    is_project=False,
 735                    is_windowed=True,
 736                    is_ordered=True,
 737                )
 738            )
 739        else:  # e and u case
 740            matches.append(
 741                data_algebra.data_ops_types.MethodUse(
 742                    row["op"],
 743                    is_project=False,
 744                    is_windowed=False,
 745                    is_ordered=False,
 746                )
 747            )
 748        if len(matches) > 0:
 749            good_use = (
 750                model_name in data_algebra.op_catalog.methods_table.columns
 751            ) and (data_algebra.op_catalog.methods_table[model_name].values[i] == "y")
 752            for m in matches:
 753                known_method_uses.add(m)
 754                if good_use:
 755                    recommended_method_uses.add(m)
 756    return known_method_uses, recommended_method_uses

 759class DBModel:
 760    """A model of how SQL should be generated for a given database."""
 761
 762    identifier_quote: str
 763    string_quote: str
 764    on_start: str
 765    on_end: str
 766    on_joiner: str
 767    drop_text: str
 768    string_type: str
 769    supports_with: bool
 770    supports_cte_elim: bool
 771    allow_extend_merges: bool
 772    default_SQL_format_options: SQLFormatOptions
 773    union_all_term_start: str
 774    union_all_term_end: str
 775    known_methods: Optional[Set[data_algebra.data_ops_types.MethodUse]]
 776    recommended_methods: Optional[Set[data_algebra.data_ops_types.MethodUse]]
 777
 778    def __init__(
 779        self,
 780        *,
 781        identifier_quote: str = '"',
 782        string_quote: str = "'",
 783        sql_formatters=None,
 784        op_replacements=None,
 785        local_data_model=None,
 786        on_start: str = "",
 787        on_end: str = "",
 788        on_joiner: str = "AND",
 789        drop_text: str = "DROP TABLE",
 790        string_type: str = "VARCHAR",
 791        float_type: str = "FLOAT64",
 792        supports_with: bool = True,
 793        supports_cte_elim: bool = True,
 794        allow_extend_merges: bool = True,
 795        default_SQL_format_options=None,
 796        union_all_term_start: str = "(",
 797        union_all_term_end: str = ")",
 798    ):
 799        if local_data_model is None:
 800            local_data_model = data_algebra.default_data_model
 801        self.local_data_model = local_data_model
 802        if sql_formatters is None:
 803            sql_formatters = {}
 804        assert identifier_quote != string_quote
 805        self.identifier_quote = identifier_quote
 806        self.string_quote = string_quote
 807        self.sql_formatters = sql_formatters.copy()
 808        for k in db_expr_formatters.keys():
 809            if k not in self.sql_formatters.keys():
 810                self.sql_formatters[k] = db_expr_formatters[k]
 811        if op_replacements is None:
 812            op_replacements = db_default_op_replacements
 813        self.op_replacements = op_replacements.copy()
 814        self.on_start = on_start
 815        self.on_end = on_end
 816        self.on_joiner = on_joiner
 817        self.drop_text = drop_text
 818        self.string_type = string_type
 819        self.float_type = float_type
 820        if default_SQL_format_options is None:
 821            default_SQL_format_options = SQLFormatOptions()
 822        assert isinstance(default_SQL_format_options, SQLFormatOptions)
 823        self.default_SQL_format_options = default_SQL_format_options
 824        self.supports_with = supports_with
 825        self.supports_cte_elim = supports_cte_elim and supports_with
 826        self.allow_extend_merges = allow_extend_merges
 827        self.union_all_term_start = union_all_term_start
 828        self.union_all_term_end = union_all_term_end
 829        self.known_methods = None
 830        self.recommended_methods = None
 831        if str(self) in data_algebra.op_catalog.methods_table.columns:
 832            k_meth, r_meth = _annotated_method_catalogue(str(self))
 833            assert k_meth is not None  # type hint
 834            assert r_meth is not None  # type hint
 835            self.known_methods = k_meth
 836            self.recommended_methods = r_meth

 839        """

 841        :param conn: database connection

 847        """
 848        Do any augmentation or preperation of a database connection. Example: adding stored procedures.

 850        pass

 854    # noinspection PyMethodMayBeStatic
 855    def execute(self, conn, q):
 856        """
 857
 858        :param conn: database connectionex
 859        :param q: sql query
 860        """
 861        if isinstance(q, data_algebra.data_ops.ViewRepresentation):
 862            q = q.to_sql(db_model=self)
 863        else:
 864            q = str(q)
 865        assert isinstance(q, str)
 866        pandas.io.sql.execute(q, conn)
 867
 868    def read_query(self, conn, q):
 869        """
 870
 871        :param conn: database connection
 872        :param q: sql query
 873        :return: query results as table
 874        """
 875        if isinstance(q, data_algebra.data_ops.ViewRepresentation):
 876            q = q.to_sql(db_model=self)
 877        else:
 878            q = str(q)
 879        assert isinstance(q, str)
 880        r = pandas.io.sql.read_sql(q, conn)
 881        r = self.local_data_model.pd.DataFrame(r)
 882        r = r.reset_index(drop=True)
 883        return r
 884
 885    def table_exists(self, conn, table_name: str) -> bool:
 886        """
 887        Return true if table exists.
 888        """
 889        assert isinstance(table_name, str)
 890        q_table_name = self.quote_table_name(table_name)
 891        table_exists = True
 892        # noinspection PyBroadException
 893        try:
 894            self.read_query(conn, "SELECT * FROM " + q_table_name + " LIMIT 1")
 895        except Exception:
 896            table_exists = False
 897        return table_exists
 898
 899    def drop_table(self, conn, table_name: str, *, check: bool = True) -> None:
 900        """
 901        Remove a table.
 902        """
 903        if (not check) or self.table_exists(conn, table_name):
 904            q_table_name = self.quote_table_name(table_name)
 905            self.execute(conn, self.drop_text + " " + q_table_name)
 906
 907    # noinspection PyMethodMayBeStatic,SqlNoDataSourceInspection
 908    def insert_table(
 909        self, conn, d, table_name: str, *, qualifiers=None, allow_overwrite=False
 910    ) -> None:
 911        """
 912        Insert a table.
 913
 914        :param conn: a database connection
 915        :param d: a Pandas table
 916        :param table_name: name to give write to
 917        :param qualifiers: schema and such
 918        :param allow_overwrite logical, if True drop previous table
 919        """
 920
 921        if qualifiers is not None:
 922            raise ValueError("non-empty qualifiers not yet supported on insert")
 923        if self.table_exists(conn, table_name):
 924            if not allow_overwrite:
 925                raise ValueError("table " + table_name + " already exists")
 926            else:
 927                self.drop_table(conn, table_name, check=False)
 928        # Note: the Pandas to_sql() method appears to have SQLite hard-wired into it
 929        # it refers to sqlite_master
 930        # this behavior seems to change if sqlalchemy is active
 931        d.to_sql(name=table_name, con=conn, index=False)
 932
 933    # noinspection PyMethodMayBeStatic,PyUnusedLocal
 934    def read_table(self, conn, table_name: str, *, qualifiers=None, limit=None):
 935        """
 936        Return table contents as a Pandas data frame.
 937        """
 938        assert isinstance(table_name, str)
 939        q_table_name = self.quote_table_name(table_name)
 940        sql = "SELECT * FROM " + q_table_name
 941        if limit is not None:
 942            sql = sql + " LIMIT " + limit.__repr__()
 943        return self.read_query(conn, sql)
 944
 945    def read(self, conn, table):
 946        """
 947        Return table as a pandas data frame for table description.
 948        """
 949        if table.node_name != "TableDescription":
 950            raise TypeError(
 951                "Expect table to be a data_algebra.data_ops.TableDescription"
 952            )
 953        return self.read_table(
 954            conn=conn, table_name=table.table_name, qualifiers=table.qualifiers
 955        )
 956
 957    def quote_identifier(self, identifier: str) -> str:
 958        """
 959        Quote identifier.
 960        """
 961        assert isinstance(identifier, str)
 962        if self.identifier_quote in identifier:
 963            raise ValueError(
 964                "did not expect " + self.identifier_quote + " in identifier"
 965            )
 966        return self.identifier_quote + identifier + self.identifier_quote
 967
 968    def quote_table_name(self, table_description) -> str:
 969        """
 970        Quote a table name.
 971        """
 972        if not isinstance(table_description, str):
 973            try:
 974                if table_description.node_name == "TableDescription":
 975                    table_description = table_description.table_name
 976                else:
 977                    raise TypeError(
 978                        "Expected table_description to be a string or data_algebra.data_ops.TableDescription)"
 979                    )
 980            except KeyError:
 981                raise TypeError(
 982                    "Expected table_description to be a string or data_algebra.data_ops.TableDescription)"
 983                )
 984        return self.quote_identifier(table_description)
 985
 986    def quote_string(self, string: str) -> str:
 987        """
 988        Quote a string value.
 989        """
 990        assert isinstance(string, str)
 991        # replace all string quotes with doubled string quotes
 992        return (
 993            self.string_quote
 994            + re.sub(self.string_quote, self.string_quote + self.string_quote, string)
 995            + self.string_quote
 996        )
 997
 998    def value_to_sql(self, v) -> str:
 999        """
1000        Convert a value to valid SQL.
1001        """
1002        if v is None:
1003            return "NULL"
1004        if isinstance(v, data_algebra.expr_rep.ListTerm):
1005            return "(" + ", ".join([self.value_to_sql(vi) for vi in v.value]) + ")"
1006        if isinstance(v, data_algebra.expr_rep.Value):
1007            return self.value_to_sql(v.value)
1008        if isinstance(v, str):
1009            return self.quote_string(v)
1010        if isinstance(v, bool):
1011            if v:
1012                return "TRUE"
1013            else:
1014                return "FALSE"
1015        if isinstance(v, float):
1016            if math.isnan(v):
1017                return "NULL"  # Pandas confuses NaN and None, so we use NULL
1018            return str(v)
1019        if isinstance(v, int):
1020            return str(v)
1021        if isinstance(v, list) or isinstance(v, tuple):
1022            return "(" + ", ".join([self.value_to_sql(vi) for vi in v]) + ")"
1023        return str(v)
1024
1025    def table_values_to_sql_str_list(
1026        self, v, *, result_name: str = "table_values"
1027    ) -> List[str]:
1028        """
1029        Convert a table of values to a SQL. Only for small tables.
1030        """
1031        assert v is not None
1032        m = v.shape[0]
1033        assert m > 0
1034        n = v.shape[1]
1035        assert n > 0
1036        qi = self.quote_identifier
1037        qv = self.value_to_sql
1038
1039        def q_row(i):
1040            """quote row"""
1041            return (
1042                self.union_all_term_start
1043                + "SELECT "
1044                + ", ".join(
1045                    [
1046                        f"{qv(v[v.columns[j]][i])} AS {qi(v.columns[j])}"
1047                        for j in range(n)
1048                    ]
1049                )
1050                + self.union_all_term_end
1051            )
1052
1053        sql = (
1054            ["SELECT", " *", "FROM ("]
1055            + ["    " + ("" if (i < 1) else "UNION ALL ") + q_row(i) for i in range(m)]
1056            + [f") {qi(result_name)}"]
1057        )
1058        return sql
1059
1060    def expr_to_sql(self, expression, *, want_inline_parens: bool = False) -> str:
1061        """
1062        Convert an expression to SQL.
1063        """
1064        if isinstance(expression, str):
1065            return expression
1066        assert isinstance(expression, data_algebra.expr_rep.PreTerm)
1067        if isinstance(expression, data_algebra.expr_rep.Value):
1068            return self.value_to_sql(expression.value)
1069        if isinstance(expression, data_algebra.expr_rep.ColumnReference):
1070            return self.quote_identifier(expression.column_name)
1071        if isinstance(expression, data_algebra.expr_rep.Expression):
1072            op = expression.op
1073            if op in self.op_replacements.keys():
1074                op = self.op_replacements[op]
1075            elif op.lower() in self.op_replacements.keys():
1076                op = self.op_replacements[op.lower()]
1077            elif op.upper() in self.op_replacements.keys():
1078                op = self.op_replacements[op.upper()]
1079            if op in self.sql_formatters.keys():
1080                return self.sql_formatters[op](self, expression)
1081            if op.lower() in self.sql_formatters.keys():
1082                return self.sql_formatters[op.lower()](self, expression)
1083            if op.upper() in self.sql_formatters.keys():
1084                return self.sql_formatters[op.upper()](self, expression)
1085            if (len(expression.args) > 1) and expression.inline:
1086                subs = [
1087                    self.expr_to_sql(ai, want_inline_parens=True)
1088                    for ai in expression.args
1089                ]
1090                res = ""
1091                if want_inline_parens:
1092                    res = res + "("
1093                assert len(subs) > 0
1094                if len(subs) == 1:
1095                    res = op.upper() + subs[0]
1096                else:
1097                    res = res + (" " + op.upper() + " ").join(subs)
1098                if want_inline_parens:
1099                    res = res + ")"
1100                return res
1101            subs = [
1102                self.expr_to_sql(ai, want_inline_parens=False) for ai in expression.args
1103            ]
1104            return op.upper() + "(" + ", ".join(subs) + ")"
1105        if isinstance(expression, data_algebra.expr_rep.ListTerm):
1106            return self.value_to_sql(expression.value)
1107        raise TypeError("unexpected type: " + str(type(expression)))
1108
1109    def _indent_and_sep_terms(
1110        self, terms, *, sep: str = ",", sql_format_options=None
1111    ) -> List[str]:
1112        if sql_format_options is None:
1113            sql_format_options = self.default_SQL_format_options
1114        n = len(terms)
1115        assert n >= 1
1116        comma_spacer = " " * len(sep)
1117        if sql_format_options.initial_commas:
1118            return [
1119                sql_format_options.sql_indent
1120                + (comma_spacer if i == 0 else sep)
1121                + " "
1122                + terms[i]
1123                for i in range(n)
1124            ]
1125        return [
1126            sql_format_options.sql_indent
1127            + terms[i]
1128            + ((" " + sep) if i < (n - 1) else "")
1129            for i in range(n)
1130        ]

1132    def table_def_to_near_sql(
1133        self, table_def, *, using=None, temp_id_source=None, sql_format_options=None
1134    ) -> data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL:
1135        """
1136        Convert a table description to NearSQL.
1137        """
1138        if table_def.node_name != "TableDescription":
1139            raise TypeError(
1140                "Expected table_def to be a data_algebra.data_ops.TableDescription)"
1141            )
1142        if temp_id_source is None:
1143            temp_id_source = [0]
1144        if using is None:
1145            using = set(table_def.column_names)
1146        missing = using - OrderedSet(table_def.column_names)
1147        if len(missing) > 0:
1148            raise KeyError("referred to unknown columns: " + str(missing))
1149        cols_using = [c for c in table_def.column_names if c in using]
1150        subsql = data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQLTable(
1151            terms={k: self.quote_identifier(k) for k in cols_using},
1152            table_name=self.quote_table_name(table_def),
1153            quoted_table_name=self.quote_table_name(table_def),
1154        )
1155        near_sql = subsql
1156        if (len(using) > 0) and (
1157            not (set([k for k in using]) == set([k for k in table_def.column_names]))
1158        ):
1159            # need a non-trivial select here
1160            terms = OrderedDict()
1161            for k in using:
1162                terms[k] = k  # these get quoted later
1163            view_name = "table_reference_" + str(temp_id_source[0])
1164            temp_id_source[0] = temp_id_source[0] + 1
1165            return data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQLUnaryStep(
1166                terms=terms,
1167                query_name=view_name,
1168                quoted_query_name=self.quote_identifier(view_name),
1169                sub_sql=subsql.to_bound_near_sql(columns=using),
1170                ops_key=f"table({table_def.table_name}, {terms.keys()})",
1171            )
1172        return near_sql
1173
1174    def extend_to_near_sql(
1175        self, extend_node, *, using=None, temp_id_source=None, sql_format_options=None
1176    ) -> data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL:
1177        """
1178        Convert an extend step into NearSQL.
1179        """
1180        if extend_node.node_name != "ExtendNode":
1181            raise TypeError(
1182                "Expected extend_node to be a data_algebra.data_ops.ExtendNode)"
1183            )
1184        if temp_id_source is None:
1185            temp_id_source = [0]
1186        if using is None:
1187            using = OrderedSet(extend_node.column_names)
1188        using = using.union(
1189            extend_node.partition_by, extend_node.order_by, extend_node.reverse
1190        )
1191        subops = OrderedDict()
1192        for (k, op) in extend_node.ops.items():
1193            if k in using:
1194                subops[k] = op
1195        if len(subops) <= 0:
1196            # using was not None is this case as len(extend_node.ops)>0 and all keys are in extend_node.column_names
1197            return extend_node.sources[0].to_near_sql_implementation_(
1198                db_model=self, using=using, temp_id_source=temp_id_source
1199            )
1200        if len(using) < 1:
1201            raise ValueError("must produce at least one column")
1202        missing = using - set(extend_node.column_names)
1203        if len(missing) > 0:
1204            raise KeyError("referred to unknown columns: " + str(missing))
1205        # get set of columns we need from subquery
1206        subusing = extend_node.columns_used_from_sources(using=using)[0]
1207        subsql = extend_node.sources[0].to_near_sql_implementation_(
1208            db_model=self, using=subusing, temp_id_source=temp_id_source
1209        )
1210        window_term = ""
1211        window_vars = set()
1212        if (
1213            extend_node.windowed_situation
1214            or (len(extend_node.partition_by) > 0)
1215            or (len(extend_node.order_by) > 0)
1216        ):
1217            window_term = " OVER ( "
1218            if len(extend_node.partition_by) > 0:
1219                pt = [self.quote_identifier(ci) for ci in extend_node.partition_by]
1220                window_term = window_term + "PARTITION BY " + ", ".join(pt) + " "
1221                window_vars.update(extend_node.partition_by)
1222            if len(extend_node.order_by) > 0:
1223                revs = set(extend_node.reverse)
1224                rt = [
1225                    self.quote_identifier(ci) + (" DESC" if ci in revs else "")
1226                    for ci in extend_node.order_by
1227                ]
1228                window_term = window_term + "ORDER BY " + ", ".join(rt) + " "
1229                window_vars.update(extend_node.order_by)
1230            window_term = window_term + " ) "
1231        terms: Dict[str, Optional[str]] = OrderedDict()
1232        declared_term_dependencies = OrderedDict()
1233        origcols = [k for k in using if k not in subops.keys()]
1234        for k in origcols:
1235            terms[k] = None
1236            declared_term_dependencies[k] = {k}
1237        for (ci, oi) in subops.items():
1238            terms[ci] = self.expr_to_sql(oi) + window_term
1239            cols_used_in_term: Set[str] = set()
1240            oi.get_column_names(cols_used_in_term)
1241            cols_used_in_term.update(window_vars)
1242            declared_term_dependencies[ci] = cols_used_in_term
1243        annotation = str(extend_node.to_python_src_(print_sources=False, indent=-1))
1244        # TODO: see if we can merge with subsql instead of building a new one
1245        if (
1246            self.allow_extend_merges
1247            and isinstance(subsql, data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQLUnaryStep)
1248            and subsql.mergeable
1249            and (subsql.declared_term_dependencies is not None)
1250            and ((subsql.suffix is None) or (len(subsql.suffix) == 0))
1251        ):
1252            # check detailed merge conditions
1253            def non_trivial_terms(*, dep_dict, term_dict):
1254                """pickout non-trivial terms"""
1255                return [
1256                    ki
1257                    for ki, vi in dep_dict.items()
1258                    if (len(vi - {ki}) > 0)
1259                    or (ki not in vi)
1260                    or ((term_dict[ki] is not None) and (term_dict[ki] != ki))
1261                ]
1262
1263            our_non_trivial_terms = non_trivial_terms(
1264                dep_dict=declared_term_dependencies, term_dict=terms
1265            )
1266            our_needs = set().union(
1267                *[declared_term_dependencies[k] for k in our_non_trivial_terms]
1268            )
1269            sub_non_trivial_terms = non_trivial_terms(
1270                dep_dict=subsql.declared_term_dependencies, term_dict=subsql.terms
1271            )
1272            sub_needs = set().union(
1273                *[subsql.declared_term_dependencies[k] for k in sub_non_trivial_terms]
1274            )
1275            contention = set().union(
1276                set(our_non_trivial_terms).intersection(sub_non_trivial_terms),
1277                set(our_non_trivial_terms).intersection(sub_needs),
1278                set(sub_non_trivial_terms).intersection(our_needs),
1279            )
1280            if len(contention) == 0:
1281                # merge our stuff into subsql
1282                assert subsql.terms is not None  # type hint
1283                if subsql.annotation is None:
1284                    subsql.annotation = annotation
1285                else:
1286                    subsql.annotation = subsql.annotation + "." + annotation
1287                for k in our_non_trivial_terms:
1288                    subsql.terms[k] = terms[k]
1289                    subsql.declared_term_dependencies[k] = declared_term_dependencies[k]
1290                we_use = set.union(
1291                    set(terms.keys()), set(declared_term_dependencies.keys())
1292                )
1293                excess_sub_term_keys = set(subsql.terms.keys()) - we_use
1294                for k in excess_sub_term_keys:
1295                    del subsql.terms[k]
1296                excess_sub_declared_keys = (
1297                    set(subsql.declared_term_dependencies.keys()) - we_use
1298                )
1299                for k in excess_sub_declared_keys:
1300                    del subsql.declared_term_dependencies[k]
1301                return subsql
1302        view_name = "extend_" + str(temp_id_source[0])
1303        temp_id_source[0] = temp_id_source[0] + 1
1304        near_sql = data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQLUnaryStep(
1305            terms=terms,
1306            query_name=view_name,
1307            quoted_query_name=self.quote_identifier(view_name),
1308            sub_sql=subsql.to_bound_near_sql(columns=subusing),
1309            annotation=annotation,
1310            mergeable=True,
1311            declared_term_dependencies=declared_term_dependencies,
1312            ops_key=f"extend({extend_node}, {terms.keys()})",
1313        )
1314        return near_sql

1316    def project_to_near_sql(
1317        self, project_node, *, using=None, temp_id_source=None, sql_format_options=None
1318    ) -> data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL:
1319        """
1320        Convert a project step to NearSQL
1321        """
1322        if project_node.node_name != "ProjectNode":
1323            raise TypeError(
1324                "Expected project_node to be a data_algebra.data_ops.ProjectNode)"
1325            )

1328        if using is None:
1329            using = OrderedSet(project_node.column_names)
1330        subops = {k: op for (k, op) in project_node.ops.items() if k in using}
1331        subusing = project_node.columns_used_from_sources(using=using)[0]
1332        terms = {ci: self.expr_to_sql(oi) for (ci, oi) in subops.items()}
1333        terms.update({g: None for g in project_node.group_by})

1338        temp_id_source[0] = temp_id_source[0] + 1
1339        suffix = []
1340        if len(project_node.group_by) > 0:
1341            group_terms = [self.quote_identifier(c) for c in project_node.group_by]
1342            suffix = ["GROUP BY"] + self._indent_and_sep_terms(
1343                group_terms, sql_format_options=sql_format_options
1344            )
1345        near_sql = data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQLUnaryStep(
1346            terms=terms,
1347            query_name=view_name,
1348            quoted_query_name=self.quote_identifier(view_name),
1349            sub_sql=subsql.to_bound_near_sql(columns=subusing),
1350            suffix=suffix,
1351            annotation=str(project_node.to_python_src_(print_sources=False, indent=-1)),
1352            ops_key=f"project({project_node}, {terms.keys()})",
1353        )

1472        """
1473        Convert order rows to NearSQL.
1474        """

1480            temp_id_source = [0]

1484            using_was_None = True
1485        subusing = order_node.columns_used_from_sources(using=using)[0]
1486        subusing = [c for c in order_node.column_names if c in subusing]  # fix order

1498                suffix

1512            terms=terms,
1513            query_name=view_name,
1514            quoted_query_name=self.quote_identifier(view_name),

1519        )

1604    def _coalesce_terms(
1605        self, *, sub_view_name_first, sub_view_name_second, cols
1606    ) -> OrderedDict:
1607        coalesce_formatter = self.sql_formatters["coalesce"]
1608
1609        class PseudoExpression:
1610            """
1611            Class to carry info into a method expecting an actual expression type.
1612            """
1613
1614            def __init__(self, args):
1615                self.args = args.copy()
1616
1617        terms = OrderedDict()
1618        for ci in cols:
1619            terms[ci] = coalesce_formatter(
1620                self,
1621                PseudoExpression(
1622                    [
1623                        sub_view_name_first + "." + self.quote_identifier(ci),
1624                        sub_view_name_second + "." + self.quote_identifier(ci),
1625                    ]
1626                ),
1627            )
1628        return terms

1630    def _natural_join_sub_queries(
1631        self, *, join_node, using, temp_id_source: List
1632    ) -> Tuple[
1633        OrderedSet,
1634        data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL,
1635        OrderedSet,
1636        data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL,
1637    ]:
1638        if join_node.node_name != "NaturalJoinNode":
1639            raise TypeError(
1640                "Expected join_node to be a data_algebra.data_ops.NaturalJoinNode)"
1641            )
1642        if using is None:
1643            using = OrderedSet(join_node.column_names)
1644        if len(using) < 1:
1645            raise ValueError("join must use or select at least one column")
1646        missing = using - set(join_node.column_names)
1647        if len(missing) > 0:
1648            raise KeyError("referred to unknown columns: " + str(missing))
1649        using_left, using_right = join_node.columns_used_from_sources(
1650            using=using.union(join_node.on_a).union(join_node.on_b)
1651        )
1652        sql_left = join_node.sources[0].to_near_sql_implementation_(
1653            db_model=self, using=using_left, temp_id_source=temp_id_source
1654        )
1655        sql_right = join_node.sources[1].to_near_sql_implementation_(
1656            db_model=self, using=using_right, temp_id_source=temp_id_source
1657        )
1658        return using_left, sql_left, using_right, sql_right
1659
1660    def natural_join_to_near_sql(
1661        self,
1662        join_node,
1663        *,
1664        using=None,
1665        temp_id_source=None,
1666        sql_format_options=None,
1667        left_is_first=True,
1668    ) -> data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL:
1669        """
1670        Convert natural join into NearSQL.
1671        """
1672        if temp_id_source is None:
1673            temp_id_source = [0]
1674        if using is None:
1675            using = OrderedSet(join_node.column_names)
1676        view_name = f"natural_join_{temp_id_source[0]}"
1677        left_q = f"join_source_left_{temp_id_source[0]}"
1678        right_q = f"join_source_right_{temp_id_source[0]}"
1679        temp_id_source[0] = temp_id_source[0] + 1
1680        using_left, sql_left, using_right, sql_right = self._natural_join_sub_queries(
1681            join_node=join_node, using=using, temp_id_source=temp_id_source
1682        )
1683        left_qqn = self.quote_identifier(left_q)
1684        right_qqn = self.quote_identifier(right_q)
1685        common = using_left.intersection(using_right)
1686        if left_is_first:
1687            terms = self._coalesce_terms(
1688                sub_view_name_first=left_qqn,
1689                sub_view_name_second=right_qqn,
1690                cols=[ci for ci in common if ci in using],
1691            )
1692        else:
1693            terms = self._coalesce_terms(
1694                sub_view_name_first=right_qqn,
1695                sub_view_name_second=left_qqn,
1696                cols=[ci for ci in common if ci in using],
1697            )
1698        for ci in using_left:
1699            if ci not in common:
1700                terms[ci] = None
1701        for ci in using_right:
1702            if ci not in common:
1703                terms[ci] = None
1704        on_terms = []
1705        if len(join_node.on_a) > 0:
1706            on_terms = ["ON " + self.on_start] + self._indent_and_sep_terms(
1707                [
1708                    left_qqn
1709                    + "."
1710                    + self.quote_identifier(c_a)
1711                    + " = "
1712                    + right_qqn
1713                    + "."
1714                    + self.quote_identifier(c_b)
1715                    for c_a, c_b in zip(join_node.on_a, join_node.on_b)
1716                ],
1717                sep=self.on_joiner,
1718                sql_format_options=sql_format_options,
1719            )
1720            if (self.on_end is not None) and (len(self.on_end) > 0):
1721                on_terms = on_terms + [self.on_end]
1722        near_sql = data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQLBinaryStep(
1723            terms=terms,
1724            query_name=view_name,
1725            quoted_query_name=self.quote_identifier(view_name),
1726            sub_sql1=sql_left.to_bound_near_sql(
1727                columns=using_left,
1728                force_sql=False,
1729                public_name=left_q,
1730                public_name_quoted=left_qqn,
1731            ),
1732            joiner=join_node.jointype + " JOIN",
1733            sub_sql2=sql_right.to_bound_near_sql(
1734                columns=using_right,
1735                force_sql=False,
1736                public_name=right_q,
1737                public_name_quoted=right_qqn,
1738            ),
1739            suffix=on_terms,
1740            annotation=str(join_node.to_python_src_(print_sources=False, indent=-1)),
1741            ops_key=f"join({join_node}, {terms.keys()})",
1742        )
1743        return near_sql
1744
1745    def concat_rows_to_near_sql(

1764        subusing = concat_node.columns_used_from_sources(using=using)
1765        using_left = subusing[0]
1766        using_right = subusing[1]
1767        if set(using_left) != set(using_right):
1768            raise ValueError("left/right usings did not match")
1769        using_joint = using_left.copy()
1770        terms = {ci: None for ci in using_joint}
1771        expr_left = concat_node.sources[0]
1772        expr_right = concat_node.sources[1]
1773        if concat_node.id_column is not None:
1774            expr_left = expr_left.extend(
1775                {concat_node.id_column: f'"{concat_node.a_name}"'}
1776            )
1777            expr_right = expr_right.extend(
1778                {concat_node.id_column: f'"{concat_node.b_name}"'}
1779            )
1780            using_joint.add(concat_node.id_column)
1781            terms.update({concat_node.id_column: None})
1782        sql_left = expr_left.to_near_sql_implementation_(
1783            db_model=self, using=using_joint, temp_id_source=temp_id_source
1784        )
1785        sql_right = expr_right.to_near_sql_implementation_(
1786            db_model=self, using=using_joint, temp_id_source=temp_id_source
1787        )
1788        view_name = "concat_rows_" + str(temp_id_source[0])
1789        temp_id_source[0] = temp_id_source[0] + 1
1790        near_sql = data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQLBinaryStep(
1791            terms=terms,
1792            query_name=view_name,
1793            quoted_query_name=self.quote_identifier(view_name),
1794            sub_sql1=sql_left.to_bound_near_sql(
1795                columns=using_joint.copy(), force_sql=True
1796            ),
1797            joiner="UNION ALL",
1798            sub_sql2=sql_right.to_bound_near_sql(
1799                columns=using_joint.copy(), force_sql=True
1800            ),
1801            annotation=str(concat_node.to_python_src_(print_sources=False, indent=-1)),
1802            ops_key=f"concat({concat_node}, {terms.keys()})",
1803        )
1804        return near_sql
1805
1806    def non_known_methods(
1807        self, ops: data_algebra.data_ops.ViewRepresentation
1808    ) -> List[data_algebra.data_ops_types.MethodUse]:
1809        """Return list of used non-recommended methods."""
1810        if self.known_methods is None:
1811            return []  # can't check, just pass
1812        method_uses = ops.methods_used()
1813        non_recommended = [op for op in method_uses if op not in self.known_methods]
1814        non_recommended.sort()
1815        return non_recommended
1816
1817    def non_recommended_methods(
1818        self, ops: data_algebra.data_ops.ViewRepresentation
1819    ) -> List[data_algebra.data_ops_types.MethodUse]:
1820        """Return list of used non-recommended methods."""
1821        if (self.recommended_methods is None) or (self.known_methods is None):
1822            return []  # can't check, just pass
1823        method_uses = ops.methods_used()
1824        non_recommended = [
1825            op
1826            for op in method_uses
1827            if (op not in self.recommended_methods) and (op in self.known_methods)
1828        ]
1829        return non_recommended

1831    def to_sql(
1832        self,
1833        ops: data_algebra.data_ops.ViewRepresentation,
1834        *,
1835        sql_format_options: Optional[SQLFormatOptions] = None,
1836    ) -> str:
1837        """
1838        Convert ViewRepresentation into SQL string.
1839
1840        :param ops: ViewRepresentation to convert
1841        :param sql_format_options: sql formatting options
1842        :return: sql string
1843        """
1844        assert isinstance(self, DBModel)
1845        assert isinstance(ops, data_algebra.data_ops.ViewRepresentation)
1846        if sql_format_options is None:
1847            sql_format_options = self.default_SQL_format_options
1848        assert isinstance(sql_format_options, SQLFormatOptions)
1849        ops.columns_used()  # for table consistency check/raise
1850        if sql_format_options.warn_on_novel_methods:
1851            non_known = self.non_known_methods(ops)
1852            if len(non_known) > 0:
1853                warnings.warn(
1854                    f"{self} translation using undocumented method context: {non_known}",
1855                    UserWarning,
1856                )
1857        if sql_format_options.warn_on_method_support:
1858            non_rec = self.non_recommended_methods(ops)
1859            if len(non_rec) > 0:
1860                warnings.warn(
1861                    f"{self} translation doesn't fully support method context: {non_rec}",
1862                    UserWarning,
1863                )
1864        # TODO: put common sub-expression control object here and pass into converters
1865        temp_id_source = [0]
1866        near_sql = ops.to_near_sql_implementation_(
1867            db_model=self, using=None, temp_id_source=temp_id_source
1868        )
1869        assert isinstance(near_sql, data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL)
1870        sql_str_list = None
1871        if sql_format_options.use_with and self.supports_with:
1872            cte_cache: Optional[Dict] = None
1873            if (
1874                sql_format_options.use_cte_elim
1875                and self.supports_with
1876                and self.supports_cte_elim
1877            ):
1878                cte_cache = dict()
1879            sequence = near_sql.to_with_form(cte_cache=cte_cache)
1880            len_sequence = len(sequence.previous_steps)
1881            # can fall back to the non-with path
1882            if len(sequence.previous_steps) >= 1:
1883                sql_sequence: List[str] = []
1884                for i in range(len_sequence):
1885                    nmi = sequence.previous_steps[i][0]  # already quoted
1886                    sqli = sequence.previous_steps[i][1].convert_subsql(
1887                        db_model=self, sql_format_options=sql_format_options
1888                    )
1889                    sql_sequence = (
1890                        sql_sequence
1891                        + [f"{sql_format_options.sql_indent}{nmi} AS ("]
1892                        + [
1893                            sql_format_options.sql_indent
1894                            + sql_format_options.sql_indent
1895                            + s
1896                            for s in sqli
1897                        ]
1898                    )
1899                    if i < (len_sequence - 1):
1900                        sql_sequence = sql_sequence + [
1901                            sql_format_options.sql_indent + ") ,"
1902                        ]
1903                    else:
1904                        sql_sequence = sql_sequence + [
1905                            sql_format_options.sql_indent + ")"
1906                        ]
1907                sql_last = sequence.last_step.to_sql_str_list(
1908                    db_model=self, force_sql=True, sql_format_options=sql_format_options
1909                )
1910                sql_str_list = ["WITH"] + sql_sequence + sql_last
1911        if sql_str_list is None:
1912            # non-with path
1913            sql_str_list = near_sql.to_sql_str_list(
1914                db_model=self, force_sql=True, sql_format_options=sql_format_options
1915            )
1916        if sql_format_options.annotate:
1917            model_descr = re.sub(r"\s+", " ", str(self))
1918            sql_str_list = [
1919                f"-- data_algebra SQL https://github.com/WinVector/data_algebra",
1920                f"--  dialect: {model_descr} {data_algebra.__version__}",
1921                f"--       string quote: {self.string_quote}",
1922                f"--   identifier quote: {self.identifier_quote}",
1923            ] + sql_str_list
1924        sql_str_list = [v.rstrip() for v in sql_str_list]
1925        sql_str_list = [v for v in sql_str_list if len(v) > 0]
1926        return "\n".join(sql_str_list) + "\n"

1928    def row_recs_to_blocks_query_str_list_pair(
1929        self, record_spec
1930    ) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
1931        """
1932        Convert row recs to blocks transformation into structures to help with SQL conversion.
1933        """
1934        control_value_cols = [
1935            c
1936            for c in record_spec.control_table.columns
1937            if c not in record_spec.control_table_keys
1938        ]
1939        control_cols = [
1940            "a." + self.quote_identifier(c) for c in record_spec.record_keys
1941        ] + [
1942            "b." + self.quote_identifier(key_col)
1943            for key_col in record_spec.control_table_keys
1944        ]
1945        col_stmts = []
1946        for c in record_spec.record_keys:
1947            col_stmts.append(
1948                " a." + self.quote_identifier(c) + " AS " + self.quote_identifier(c)
1949            )
1950        for key_col in record_spec.control_table_keys:
1951            col_stmts.append(
1952                " b."
1953                + self.quote_identifier(key_col)
1954                + " AS "
1955                + self.quote_identifier(key_col)
1956            )
1957        seen = set()
1958        for result_col in control_value_cols:
1959            if result_col in seen:
1960                continue
1961            seen.add(result_col)
1962            cstmt = " CASE "
1963            col = record_spec.control_table[result_col]
1964            isnull = col.isnull()
1965            for i in range(len(col)):
1966                if not (isnull[i]):
1967                    source_col = col[i]
1968                    col_sql = (
1969                        "  WHEN CAST(b."
1970                        + self.quote_identifier(result_col)
1971                        + " AS "
1972                        + self.string_type
1973                        + ") = "
1974                        + self.quote_string(str(source_col))
1975                        + " THEN a."
1976                        + self.quote_identifier(source_col)
1977                        + " "
1978                    )
1979                    cstmt = cstmt + col_sql
1980            cstmt = cstmt + " ELSE NULL END AS " + self.quote_identifier(result_col)
1981            col_stmts.append(cstmt)
1982        ctab_sql = self.table_values_to_sql_str_list(record_spec.control_table)
1983        sql_prefix = _list_join_expecting_list(",", col_stmts) + [
1984            "FROM ( SELECT * FROM "
1985        ]
1986        sql_suffix = (
1987            [" ) a"]
1988            + ["CROSS JOIN ("]
1989            + _list_join_expecting_list("", ctab_sql)
1990            + [" ) b"]
1991            + [" ORDER BY"]  # order by not required, but nice to have
1992            + _list_join_expecting_list(", ", control_cols)
1993        )
1994        return sql_prefix, sql_suffix

1996    # noinspection PyUnusedLocal
1997    def blocks_to_row_recs_query_str_list_pair(
1998        self, record_spec
1999    ) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
2000        """
2001        Convert blocks to row recs transform into structures to help with SQL translation.
2002        """
2003        assert record_spec.control_table.shape[0] >= 1
2004        col_stmts = []
2005        for c in record_spec.record_keys:
2006            col_stmts.append(
2007                " " + self.quote_identifier(c) + " AS " + self.quote_identifier(c)
2008            )
2009        if record_spec.control_table.shape[0] == 1:
2010            # special case with one row control table (rowrec)
2011            for cc in record_spec.control_table.columns:
2012                if cc not in record_spec.control_table_keys:
2013                    cc0 = record_spec.control_table[cc][0]
2014                    col_stmts.append(
2015                        " "
2016                        + self.quote_identifier(cc)
2017                        + " AS "
2018                        + self.quote_identifier(cc0)
2019                    )
2020            sql_prefix = _list_join_expecting_list(",", col_stmts) + [
2021                "FROM ( SELECT * FROM "
2022            ]
2023            sql_suffix = [" ) a"]
2024            return sql_prefix, sql_suffix
2025        control_value_cols = [
2026            c
2027            for c in record_spec.control_table.columns
2028            if c not in record_spec.control_table_keys
2029        ]
2030        control_cols = [self.quote_identifier(c) for c in record_spec.record_keys]
2031        seen = set()
2032        for i in range(record_spec.control_table.shape[0]):
2033            for vc in control_value_cols:
2034                col = record_spec.control_table[vc]
2035                isnull = col.isnull()
2036                if col[i] not in seen and not isnull[i]:
2037                    seen.add(col[i])
2038                    clauses = []
2039                    for cc in record_spec.control_table_keys:
2040                        clauses.append(
2041                            " ( CAST("
2042                            + self.quote_identifier(cc)
2043                            + " AS "
2044                            + self.string_type
2045                            + ") = "
2046                            + self.quote_string(str(record_spec.control_table[cc][i]))
2047                            + " ) "
2048                        )
2049                    cstmt = (
2050                        " MAX(CASE WHEN "
2051                        + " AND ".join(clauses)
2052                        + " THEN "
2053                        + self.quote_identifier(vc)
2054                        + " ELSE NULL END) AS "
2055                        + self.quote_identifier(col[i])
2056                    )
2057                    col_stmts.append(cstmt)
2058        sql_prefix = _list_join_expecting_list(",", col_stmts) + [
2059            "FROM ( SELECT * FROM "
2060        ]
2061        sql_suffix = (
2062            [" ) a"]
2063            + ["GROUP BY"]
2064            + _list_join_expecting_list(",", control_cols)
2065            + ["ORDER BY "]  # order by not required, but nice to have
2066            + _list_join_expecting_list(",", control_cols)
2067        )
2068        return sql_prefix, sql_suffix

2070    # encode and name a term for use in a SQL expression
2071    def enc_term_(self, k, *, terms) -> str:
2072        """
2073        encode and name a term for use in a SQL expression
2074        """
2075        v = None
2076        try:
2077            v = terms[k]
2078        except KeyError:
2079            pass
2080        if (v is None) or (v == k):
2081            return self.quote_identifier(k)
2082        return v + " AS " + self.quote_identifier(k)

2424            caught = None
2425            if self.db_engine is not None:
2426                # sqlalchemy style handle
2427                # noinspection PyBroadException
2428                try:
2429                    self.db_engine.dispose()
2430                except Exception as ex:
2431                    caught = ex
2432            else:
2433                # noinspection PyBroadException
2434                try:
2435                    self.conn.close()
2436                except Exception as ex:
2437                    caught = ex

2439            self.conn = None
2440            if caught is not None:
2441                raise ValueError("close caught: " + str(caught))

 909    def insert_table(
 910        self, conn, d, table_name: str, *, qualifiers=None, allow_overwrite=False
 911    ) -> None:
 912        """
 913        Insert a table.
 914
 915        :param conn: a database connection
 916        :param d: a Pandas table
 917        :param table_name: name to give write to
 918        :param qualifiers: schema and such
 919        :param allow_overwrite logical, if True drop previous table
 920        """
 921
 922        if qualifiers is not None:
 923            raise ValueError("non-empty qualifiers not yet supported on insert")
 924        if self.table_exists(conn, table_name):
 925            if not allow_overwrite:
 926                raise ValueError("table " + table_name + " already exists")
 927            else:
 928                self.drop_table(conn, table_name, check=False)
 929        # Note: the Pandas to_sql() method appears to have SQLite hard-wired into it
 930        # it refers to sqlite_master
 931        # this behavior seems to change if sqlalchemy is active
 932        d.to_sql(name=table_name, con=conn, index=False)

 999    def value_to_sql(self, v) -> str:
1000        """
1001        Convert a value to valid SQL.
1002        """
1003        if v is None:
1004            return "NULL"
1005        if isinstance(v, data_algebra.expr_rep.ListTerm):
1006            return "(" + ", ".join([self.value_to_sql(vi) for vi in v.value]) + ")"
1007        if isinstance(v, data_algebra.expr_rep.Value):
1008            return self.value_to_sql(v.value)
1009        if isinstance(v, str):
1010            return self.quote_string(v)
1011        if isinstance(v, bool):
1012            if v:
1013                return "TRUE"
1014            else:
1015                return "FALSE"
1016        if isinstance(v, float):
1017            if math.isnan(v):
1018                return "NULL"  # Pandas confuses NaN and None, so we use NULL
1019            return str(v)
1020        if isinstance(v, int):
1021            return str(v)
1022        if isinstance(v, list) or isinstance(v, tuple):
1023            return "(" + ", ".join([self.value_to_sql(vi) for vi in v]) + ")"
1024        return str(v)

1026    def table_values_to_sql_str_list(
1027        self, v, *, result_name: str = "table_values"
1028    ) -> List[str]:
1029        """
1030        Convert a table of values to a SQL. Only for small tables.
1031        """
1032        assert v is not None
1033        m = v.shape[0]
1034        assert m > 0
1035        n = v.shape[1]
1036        assert n > 0
1037        qi = self.quote_identifier
1038        qv = self.value_to_sql
1039
1040        def q_row(i):
1041            """quote row"""
1042            return (
1043                self.union_all_term_start
1044                + "SELECT "
1045                + ", ".join(
1046                    [
1047                        f"{qv(v[v.columns[j]][i])} AS {qi(v.columns[j])}"
1048                        for j in range(n)
1049                    ]
1050                )
1051                + self.union_all_term_end
1052            )
1053
1054        sql = (
1055            ["SELECT", " *", "FROM ("]
1056            + ["    " + ("" if (i < 1) else "UNION ALL ") + q_row(i) for i in range(m)]
1057            + [f") {qi(result_name)}"]
1058        )
1059        return sql

1061    def expr_to_sql(self, expression, *, want_inline_parens: bool = False) -> str:
1062        """
1063        Convert an expression to SQL.
1064        """
1065        if isinstance(expression, str):
1066            return expression
1067        assert isinstance(expression, data_algebra.expr_rep.PreTerm)
1068        if isinstance(expression, data_algebra.expr_rep.Value):
1069            return self.value_to_sql(expression.value)
1070        if isinstance(expression, data_algebra.expr_rep.ColumnReference):
1071            return self.quote_identifier(expression.column_name)
1072        if isinstance(expression, data_algebra.expr_rep.Expression):
1073            op = expression.op
1074            if op in self.op_replacements.keys():
1075                op = self.op_replacements[op]
1076            elif op.lower() in self.op_replacements.keys():
1077                op = self.op_replacements[op.lower()]
1078            elif op.upper() in self.op_replacements.keys():
1079                op = self.op_replacements[op.upper()]
1080            if op in self.sql_formatters.keys():
1081                return self.sql_formatters[op](self, expression)
1082            if op.lower() in self.sql_formatters.keys():
1083                return self.sql_formatters[op.lower()](self, expression)
1084            if op.upper() in self.sql_formatters.keys():
1085                return self.sql_formatters[op.upper()](self, expression)
1086            if (len(expression.args) > 1) and expression.inline:
1087                subs = [
1088                    self.expr_to_sql(ai, want_inline_parens=True)
1089                    for ai in expression.args
1090                ]
1091                res = ""
1092                if want_inline_parens:
1093                    res = res + "("
1094                assert len(subs) > 0
1095                if len(subs) == 1:
1096                    res = op.upper() + subs[0]
1097                else:
1098                    res = res + (" " + op.upper() + " ").join(subs)
1099                if want_inline_parens:
1100                    res = res + ")"
1101                return res
1102            subs = [
1103                self.expr_to_sql(ai, want_inline_parens=False) for ai in expression.args
1104            ]
1105            return op.upper() + "(" + ", ".join(subs) + ")"
1106        if isinstance(expression, data_algebra.expr_rep.ListTerm):
1107            return self.value_to_sql(expression.value)
1108        raise TypeError("unexpected type: " + str(type(expression)))

1110    def _indent_and_sep_terms(
1111        self, terms, *, sep: str = ",", sql_format_options=None
1112    ) -> List[str]:
1113        if sql_format_options is None:
1114            sql_format_options = self.default_SQL_format_options
1115        n = len(terms)
1116        assert n >= 1
1117        comma_spacer = " " * len(sep)
1118        if sql_format_options.initial_commas:
1119            return [
1120                sql_format_options.sql_indent
1121                + (comma_spacer if i == 0 else sep)
1122                + " "
1123                + terms[i]
1124                for i in range(n)
1125            ]
1126        return [
1127            sql_format_options.sql_indent
1128            + terms[i]
1129            + ((" " + sep) if i < (n - 1) else "")
1130            for i in range(n)
1131        ]

1133    def table_def_to_near_sql(
1134        self, table_def, *, using=None, temp_id_source=None, sql_format_options=None
1135    ) -> data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL:
1136        """
1137        Convert a table description to NearSQL.
1138        """
1139        if table_def.node_name != "TableDescription":
1140            raise TypeError(
1141                "Expected table_def to be a data_algebra.data_ops.TableDescription)"
1142            )
1143        if temp_id_source is None:
1144            temp_id_source = [0]
1145        if using is None:
1146            using = set(table_def.column_names)
1147        missing = using - OrderedSet(table_def.column_names)
1148        if len(missing) > 0:
1149            raise KeyError("referred to unknown columns: " + str(missing))
1150        cols_using = [c for c in table_def.column_names if c in using]
1151        subsql = data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQLTable(
1152            terms={k: self.quote_identifier(k) for k in cols_using},
1153            table_name=self.quote_table_name(table_def),
1154            quoted_table_name=self.quote_table_name(table_def),
1155        )
1156        near_sql = subsql
1157        if (len(using) > 0) and (
1158            not (set([k for k in using]) == set([k for k in table_def.column_names]))
1159        ):
1160            # need a non-trivial select here
1161            terms = OrderedDict()
1162            for k in using:
1163                terms[k] = k  # these get quoted later
1164            view_name = "table_reference_" + str(temp_id_source[0])
1165            temp_id_source[0] = temp_id_source[0] + 1
1166            return data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQLUnaryStep(
1167                terms=terms,
1168                query_name=view_name,
1169                quoted_query_name=self.quote_identifier(view_name),
1170                sub_sql=subsql.to_bound_near_sql(columns=using),
1171                ops_key=f"table({table_def.table_name}, {terms.keys()})",
1172            )
1173        return near_sql

1175    def extend_to_near_sql(
1176        self, extend_node, *, using=None, temp_id_source=None, sql_format_options=None
1177    ) -> data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL:
1178        """
1179        Convert an extend step into NearSQL.
1180        """
1181        if extend_node.node_name != "ExtendNode":
1182            raise TypeError(
1183                "Expected extend_node to be a data_algebra.data_ops.ExtendNode)"
1184            )
1185        if temp_id_source is None:
1186            temp_id_source = [0]
1187        if using is None:
1188            using = OrderedSet(extend_node.column_names)
1189        using = using.union(
1190            extend_node.partition_by, extend_node.order_by, extend_node.reverse
1191        )
1192        subops = OrderedDict()
1193        for (k, op) in extend_node.ops.items():
1194            if k in using:
1195                subops[k] = op
1196        if len(subops) <= 0:
1197            # using was not None is this case as len(extend_node.ops)>0 and all keys are in extend_node.column_names
1198            return extend_node.sources[0].to_near_sql_implementation_(
1199                db_model=self, using=using, temp_id_source=temp_id_source
1200            )
1201        if len(using) < 1:
1202            raise ValueError("must produce at least one column")
1203        missing = using - set(extend_node.column_names)
1204        if len(missing) > 0:
1205            raise KeyError("referred to unknown columns: " + str(missing))
1206        # get set of columns we need from subquery
1207        subusing = extend_node.columns_used_from_sources(using=using)[0]
1208        subsql = extend_node.sources[0].to_near_sql_implementation_(
1209            db_model=self, using=subusing, temp_id_source=temp_id_source
1210        )
1211        window_term = ""
1212        window_vars = set()
1213        if (
1214            extend_node.windowed_situation
1215            or (len(extend_node.partition_by) > 0)
1216            or (len(extend_node.order_by) > 0)
1217        ):
1218            window_term = " OVER ( "
1219            if len(extend_node.partition_by) > 0:
1220                pt = [self.quote_identifier(ci) for ci in extend_node.partition_by]
1221                window_term = window_term + "PARTITION BY " + ", ".join(pt) + " "
1222                window_vars.update(extend_node.partition_by)
1223            if len(extend_node.order_by) > 0:
1224                revs = set(extend_node.reverse)
1225                rt = [
1226                    self.quote_identifier(ci) + (" DESC" if ci in revs else "")
1227                    for ci in extend_node.order_by
1228                ]
1229                window_term = window_term + "ORDER BY " + ", ".join(rt) + " "
1230                window_vars.update(extend_node.order_by)
1231            window_term = window_term + " ) "
1232        terms: Dict[str, Optional[str]] = OrderedDict()
1233        declared_term_dependencies = OrderedDict()
1234        origcols = [k for k in using if k not in subops.keys()]
1235        for k in origcols:
1236            terms[k] = None
1237            declared_term_dependencies[k] = {k}
1238        for (ci, oi) in subops.items():
1239            terms[ci] = self.expr_to_sql(oi) + window_term
1240            cols_used_in_term: Set[str] = set()
1241            oi.get_column_names(cols_used_in_term)
1242            cols_used_in_term.update(window_vars)
1243            declared_term_dependencies[ci] = cols_used_in_term
1244        annotation = str(extend_node.to_python_src_(print_sources=False, indent=-1))
1245        # TODO: see if we can merge with subsql instead of building a new one
1246        if (
1247            self.allow_extend_merges
1248            and isinstance(subsql, data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQLUnaryStep)
1249            and subsql.mergeable
1250            and (subsql.declared_term_dependencies is not None)
1251            and ((subsql.suffix is None) or (len(subsql.suffix) == 0))
1252        ):
1253            # check detailed merge conditions
1254            def non_trivial_terms(*, dep_dict, term_dict):
1255                """pickout non-trivial terms"""
1256                return [
1257                    ki
1258                    for ki, vi in dep_dict.items()
1259                    if (len(vi - {ki}) > 0)
1260                    or (ki not in vi)
1261                    or ((term_dict[ki] is not None) and (term_dict[ki] != ki))
1262                ]
1263
1264            our_non_trivial_terms = non_trivial_terms(
1265                dep_dict=declared_term_dependencies, term_dict=terms
1266            )
1267            our_needs = set().union(
1268                *[declared_term_dependencies[k] for k in our_non_trivial_terms]
1269            )
1270            sub_non_trivial_terms = non_trivial_terms(
1271                dep_dict=subsql.declared_term_dependencies, term_dict=subsql.terms
1272            )
1273            sub_needs = set().union(
1274                *[subsql.declared_term_dependencies[k] for k in sub_non_trivial_terms]
1275            )
1276            contention = set().union(
1277                set(our_non_trivial_terms).intersection(sub_non_trivial_terms),
1278                set(our_non_trivial_terms).intersection(sub_needs),
1279                set(sub_non_trivial_terms).intersection(our_needs),
1280            )
1281            if len(contention) == 0:
1282                # merge our stuff into subsql
1283                assert subsql.terms is not None  # type hint
1284                if subsql.annotation is None:
1285                    subsql.annotation = annotation
1286                else:
1287                    subsql.annotation = subsql.annotation + "." + annotation
1288                for k in our_non_trivial_terms:
1289                    subsql.terms[k] = terms[k]
1290                    subsql.declared_term_dependencies[k] = declared_term_dependencies[k]
1291                we_use = set.union(
1292                    set(terms.keys()), set(declared_term_dependencies.keys())
1293                )
1294                excess_sub_term_keys = set(subsql.terms.keys()) - we_use
1295                for k in excess_sub_term_keys:
1296                    del subsql.terms[k]
1297                excess_sub_declared_keys = (
1298                    set(subsql.declared_term_dependencies.keys()) - we_use
1299                )
1300                for k in excess_sub_declared_keys:
1301                    del subsql.declared_term_dependencies[k]
1302                return subsql
1303        view_name = "extend_" + str(temp_id_source[0])
1304        temp_id_source[0] = temp_id_source[0] + 1
1305        near_sql = data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQLUnaryStep(
1306            terms=terms,
1307            query_name=view_name,
1308            quoted_query_name=self.quote_identifier(view_name),
1309            sub_sql=subsql.to_bound_near_sql(columns=subusing),
1310            annotation=annotation,
1311            mergeable=True,
1312            declared_term_dependencies=declared_term_dependencies,
1313            ops_key=f"extend({extend_node}, {terms.keys()})",
1314        )
1315        return near_sql

1317    def project_to_near_sql(
1318        self, project_node, *, using=None, temp_id_source=None, sql_format_options=None
1319    ) -> data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL:
1320        """
1321        Convert a project step to NearSQL
1322        """
1323        if project_node.node_name != "ProjectNode":
1324            raise TypeError(
1325                "Expected project_node to be a data_algebra.data_ops.ProjectNode)"
1326            )

1328            temp_id_source = [0]
1329        if using is None:
1330            using = OrderedSet(project_node.column_names)
1331        subops = {k: op for (k, op) in project_node.ops.items() if k in using}
1332        subusing = project_node.columns_used_from_sources(using=using)[0]
1333        terms = {ci: self.expr_to_sql(oi) for (ci, oi) in subops.items()}
1334        terms.update({g: None for g in project_node.group_by})
1335        subsql = project_node.sources[0].to_near_sql_implementation_(

1340        suffix = []
1341        if len(project_node.group_by) > 0:
1342            group_terms = [self.quote_identifier(c) for c in project_node.group_by]
1343            suffix = ["GROUP BY"] + self._indent_and_sep_terms(
1344                group_terms, sql_format_options=sql_format_options
1345            )
1346        near_sql = data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQLUnaryStep(
1347            terms=terms,
1348            query_name=view_name,
1349            quoted_query_name=self.quote_identifier(view_name),
1350            sub_sql=subsql.to_bound_near_sql(columns=subusing),

1352            annotation=str(project_node.to_python_src_(print_sources=False, indent=-1)),
1353            ops_key=f"project({project_node}, {terms.keys()})",
1354        )
1355        return near_sql

1470    def order_to_near_sql(
1471        self, order_node, *, using=None, temp_id_source=None, sql_format_options=None
1472    ) -> data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL:
1473        """
1474        Convert order rows to NearSQL.
1475        """
1476        if order_node.node_name != "OrderRowsNode":
1477            raise TypeError(
1478                "Expected order_node to be a data_algebra.data_ops.OrderRowsNode)"
1479            )
1480        if temp_id_source is None:
1481            temp_id_source = [0]
1482        using_was_None = False
1483        if using is None:
1484            using = OrderedSet(order_node.column_names)
1485            using_was_None = True
1486        subusing = order_node.columns_used_from_sources(using=using)[0]
1487        subusing = [c for c in order_node.column_names if c in subusing]  # fix order
1488        subsql = order_node.sources[0].to_near_sql_implementation_(
1489            db_model=self, using=set(subusing), temp_id_source=temp_id_source
1490        )
1491        view_name = "order_rows_" + str(temp_id_source[0])
1492        temp_id_source[0] = temp_id_source[0] + 1
1493        terms = None
1494        if not using_was_None:
1495            terms = {ci: None for ci in subusing}
1496        suffix: List[str] = []
1497        if len(order_node.order_columns) > 0:
1498            suffix = (
1499                suffix
1500                + ["ORDER BY"]
1501                + self._indent_and_sep_terms(
1502                    [
1503                        self.quote_identifier(ci)
1504                        + (" DESC" if ci in set(order_node.reverse) else "")
1505                        for ci in order_node.order_columns
1506                    ],
1507                    sql_format_options=sql_format_options,
1508                )
1509            )
1510        if order_node.limit is not None:
1511            suffix = suffix + ["LIMIT " + order_node.limit.__repr__()]
1512        near_sql = data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQLUnaryStep(
1513            terms=terms,
1514            query_name=view_name,
1515            quoted_query_name=self.quote_identifier(view_name),
1516            sub_sql=subsql.to_bound_near_sql(columns=subusing),
1517            suffix=suffix,
1518            annotation=str(order_node.to_python_src_(print_sources=False, indent=-1)),
1519            ops_key=f"order({order_node})",  # no terms
1520        )
1521        return near_sql

1605    def _coalesce_terms(
1606        self, *, sub_view_name_first, sub_view_name_second, cols
1607    ) -> OrderedDict:
1608        coalesce_formatter = self.sql_formatters["coalesce"]
1609
1610        class PseudoExpression:
1611            """
1612            Class to carry info into a method expecting an actual expression type.
1613            """
1614
1615            def __init__(self, args):
1616                self.args = args.copy()
1617
1618        terms = OrderedDict()
1619        for ci in cols:
1620            terms[ci] = coalesce_formatter(
1621                self,
1622                PseudoExpression(
1623                    [
1624                        sub_view_name_first + "." + self.quote_identifier(ci),
1625                        sub_view_name_second + "." + self.quote_identifier(ci),
1626                    ]
1627                ),
1628            )
1629        return terms
