1631    def _natural_join_sub_queries(
1632        self, *, join_node, using, temp_id_source: List
1633    ) -> Tuple[
1634        OrderedSet,
1635        data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL,
1636        OrderedSet,
1637        data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL,
1638    ]:
1639        if join_node.node_name != "NaturalJoinNode":
1640            raise TypeError(
1641                "Expected join_node to be a data_algebra.data_ops.NaturalJoinNode)"
1642            )
1643        if using is None:
1644            using = OrderedSet(join_node.column_names)
1645        if len(using) < 1:
1646            raise ValueError("join must use or select at least one column")
1647        missing = using - set(join_node.column_names)
1648        if len(missing) > 0:
1649            raise KeyError("referred to unknown columns: " + str(missing))
1650        using_left, using_right = join_node.columns_used_from_sources(
1651            using=using.union(join_node.on_a).union(join_node.on_b)
1652        )
1653        sql_left = join_node.sources[0].to_near_sql_implementation_(
1654            db_model=self, using=using_left, temp_id_source=temp_id_source
1655        )
1656        sql_right = join_node.sources[1].to_near_sql_implementation_(
1657            db_model=self, using=using_right, temp_id_source=temp_id_source
1658        )
1659        return using_left, sql_left, using_right, sql_right
1660
1661    def natural_join_to_near_sql(
1662        self,
1663        join_node,
1664        *,
1665        using=None,
1666        temp_id_source=None,
1667        sql_format_options=None,
1668        left_is_first=True,
1669    ) -> data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL:
1670        """
1671        Convert natural join into NearSQL.
1672        """
1673        if temp_id_source is None:
1674            temp_id_source = [0]
1675        if using is None:
1676            using = OrderedSet(join_node.column_names)
1677        view_name = f"natural_join_{temp_id_source[0]}"
1678        left_q = f"join_source_left_{temp_id_source[0]}"
1679        right_q = f"join_source_right_{temp_id_source[0]}"
1680        temp_id_source[0] = temp_id_source[0] + 1
1681        using_left, sql_left, using_right, sql_right = self._natural_join_sub_queries(
1682            join_node=join_node, using=using, temp_id_source=temp_id_source
1683        )
1684        left_qqn = self.quote_identifier(left_q)
1685        right_qqn = self.quote_identifier(right_q)
1686        common = using_left.intersection(using_right)
1687        if left_is_first:
1688            terms = self._coalesce_terms(
1689                sub_view_name_first=left_qqn,
1690                sub_view_name_second=right_qqn,
1691                cols=[ci for ci in common if ci in using],
1692            )
1693        else:
1694            terms = self._coalesce_terms(
1695                sub_view_name_first=right_qqn,
1696                sub_view_name_second=left_qqn,
1697                cols=[ci for ci in common if ci in using],
1698            )
1699        for ci in using_left:
1700            if ci not in common:
1701                terms[ci] = None
1702        for ci in using_right:
1703            if ci not in common:
1704                terms[ci] = None
1705        on_terms = []
1706        if len(join_node.on_a) > 0:
1707            on_terms = ["ON " + self.on_start] + self._indent_and_sep_terms(
1708                [
1709                    left_qqn
1710                    + "."
1711                    + self.quote_identifier(c_a)
1712                    + " = "
1713                    + right_qqn
1714                    + "."
1715                    + self.quote_identifier(c_b)
1716                    for c_a, c_b in zip(join_node.on_a, join_node.on_b)
1717                ],
1718                sep=self.on_joiner,
1719                sql_format_options=sql_format_options,
1720            )
1721            if (self.on_end is not None) and (len(self.on_end) > 0):
1722                on_terms = on_terms + [self.on_end]
1723        near_sql = data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQLBinaryStep(
1724            terms=terms,
1725            query_name=view_name,
1726            quoted_query_name=self.quote_identifier(view_name),
1727            sub_sql1=sql_left.to_bound_near_sql(
1728                columns=using_left,
1729                force_sql=False,
1730                public_name=left_q,
1731                public_name_quoted=left_qqn,
1732            ),
1733            joiner=join_node.jointype + " JOIN",
1734            sub_sql2=sql_right.to_bound_near_sql(
1735                columns=using_right,
1736                force_sql=False,
1737                public_name=right_q,
1738                public_name_quoted=right_qqn,
1739            ),
1740            suffix=on_terms,
1741            annotation=str(join_node.to_python_src_(print_sources=False, indent=-1)),
1742            ops_key=f"join({join_node}, {terms.keys()})",
1743        )
1744        return near_sql
1745
1746    def concat_rows_to_near_sql(
1747        self, concat_node, *, using=None, temp_id_source=None, sql_format_options=None
1748    ) -> data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL:
1749        """
1750        Convert concat rows into NearSQL.
1751        """
1752        if concat_node.node_name != "ConcatRowsNode":
1753            raise TypeError(
1754                "Expected concat_node to be a data_algebra.data_ops.ConcatRowsNode)"
1755            )
1756        if temp_id_source is None:
1757            temp_id_source = [0]
1758        if using is None:
1759            using = OrderedSet(concat_node.column_names)
1760        if len(using) < 1:
1761            raise ValueError("must select at least one column")
1762        missing = using - set(concat_node.column_names)
1763        if len(missing) > 0:
1764            raise KeyError("referred to unknown columns: " + str(missing))
1765        subusing = concat_node.columns_used_from_sources(using=using)
1766        using_left = subusing[0]
1767        using_right = subusing[1]
1768        if set(using_left) != set(using_right):
1769            raise ValueError("left/right usings did not match")
1770        using_joint = using_left.copy()
1771        terms = {ci: None for ci in using_joint}
1772        expr_left = concat_node.sources[0]
1773        expr_right = concat_node.sources[1]
1774        if concat_node.id_column is not None:
1775            expr_left = expr_left.extend(
1776                {concat_node.id_column: f'"{concat_node.a_name}"'}
1777            )
1778            expr_right = expr_right.extend(
1779                {concat_node.id_column: f'"{concat_node.b_name}"'}
1780            )
1781            using_joint.add(concat_node.id_column)
1782            terms.update({concat_node.id_column: None})
1783        sql_left = expr_left.to_near_sql_implementation_(
1784            db_model=self, using=using_joint, temp_id_source=temp_id_source
1785        )
1786        sql_right = expr_right.to_near_sql_implementation_(
1787            db_model=self, using=using_joint, temp_id_source=temp_id_source
1788        )
1789        view_name = "concat_rows_" + str(temp_id_source[0])
1790        temp_id_source[0] = temp_id_source[0] + 1
1791        near_sql = data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQLBinaryStep(
1792            terms=terms,
1793            query_name=view_name,
1794            quoted_query_name=self.quote_identifier(view_name),
1795            sub_sql1=sql_left.to_bound_near_sql(
1796                columns=using_joint.copy(), force_sql=True
1797            ),
1798            joiner="UNION ALL",
1799            sub_sql2=sql_right.to_bound_near_sql(
1800                columns=using_joint.copy(), force_sql=True
1801            ),
1802            annotation=str(concat_node.to_python_src_(print_sources=False, indent=-1)),
1803            ops_key=f"concat({concat_node}, {terms.keys()})",
1804        )
1805        return near_sql

1807    def non_known_methods(
1808        self, ops: data_algebra.data_ops.ViewRepresentation
1809    ) -> List[data_algebra.data_ops_types.MethodUse]:
1810        """Return list of used non-recommended methods."""
1811        if self.known_methods is None:
1812            return []  # can't check, just pass
1813        method_uses = ops.methods_used()
1814        non_recommended = [op for op in method_uses if op not in self.known_methods]
1815        non_recommended.sort()
1816        return non_recommended
1817
1818    def non_recommended_methods(
1819        self, ops: data_algebra.data_ops.ViewRepresentation
1820    ) -> List[data_algebra.data_ops_types.MethodUse]:
1821        """Return list of used non-recommended methods."""
1822        if (self.recommended_methods is None) or (self.known_methods is None):
1823            return []  # can't check, just pass
1824        method_uses = ops.methods_used()
1825        non_recommended = [
1826            op
1827            for op in method_uses
1828            if (op not in self.recommended_methods) and (op in self.known_methods)
1829        ]
1830        return non_recommended

1832    def to_sql(
1833        self,
1834        ops: data_algebra.data_ops.ViewRepresentation,
1835        *,
1836        sql_format_options: Optional[SQLFormatOptions] = None,
1837    ) -> str:
1838        """
1839        Convert ViewRepresentation into SQL string.
1840
1841        :param ops: ViewRepresentation to convert
1842        :param sql_format_options: sql formatting options
1843        :return: sql string
1844        """
1845        assert isinstance(self, DBModel)
1846        assert isinstance(ops, data_algebra.data_ops.ViewRepresentation)
1847        if sql_format_options is None:
1848            sql_format_options = self.default_SQL_format_options
1849        assert isinstance(sql_format_options, SQLFormatOptions)
1850        ops.columns_used()  # for table consistency check/raise
1851        if sql_format_options.warn_on_novel_methods:
1852            non_known = self.non_known_methods(ops)
1853            if len(non_known) > 0:
1854                warnings.warn(
1855                    f"{self} translation using undocumented method context: {non_known}",
1856                    UserWarning,
1857                )
1858        if sql_format_options.warn_on_method_support:
1859            non_rec = self.non_recommended_methods(ops)
1860            if len(non_rec) > 0:
1861                warnings.warn(
1862                    f"{self} translation doesn't fully support method context: {non_rec}",
1863                    UserWarning,
1864                )
1865        # TODO: put common sub-expression control object here and pass into converters
1866        temp_id_source = [0]
1867        near_sql = ops.to_near_sql_implementation_(
1868            db_model=self, using=None, temp_id_source=temp_id_source
1869        )
1870        assert isinstance(near_sql, data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL)
1871        sql_str_list = None
1872        if sql_format_options.use_with and self.supports_with:
1873            cte_cache: Optional[Dict] = None
1874            if (
1875                sql_format_options.use_cte_elim
1876                and self.supports_with
1877                and self.supports_cte_elim
1878            ):
1879                cte_cache = dict()
1880            sequence = near_sql.to_with_form(cte_cache=cte_cache)
1881            len_sequence = len(sequence.previous_steps)
1882            # can fall back to the non-with path
1883            if len(sequence.previous_steps) >= 1:
1884                sql_sequence: List[str] = []
1885                for i in range(len_sequence):
1886                    nmi = sequence.previous_steps[i][0]  # already quoted
1887                    sqli = sequence.previous_steps[i][1].convert_subsql(
1888                        db_model=self, sql_format_options=sql_format_options
1889                    )
1890                    sql_sequence = (
1891                        sql_sequence
1892                        + [f"{sql_format_options.sql_indent}{nmi} AS ("]
1893                        + [
1894                            sql_format_options.sql_indent
1895                            + sql_format_options.sql_indent
1896                            + s
1897                            for s in sqli
1898                        ]
1899                    )
1900                    if i < (len_sequence - 1):
1901                        sql_sequence = sql_sequence + [
1902                            sql_format_options.sql_indent + ") ,"
1903                        ]
1904                    else:
1905                        sql_sequence = sql_sequence + [
1906                            sql_format_options.sql_indent + ")"
1907                        ]
1908                sql_last = sequence.last_step.to_sql_str_list(
1909                    db_model=self, force_sql=True, sql_format_options=sql_format_options
1910                )
1911                sql_str_list = ["WITH"] + sql_sequence + sql_last
1912        if sql_str_list is None:
1913            # non-with path
1914            sql_str_list = near_sql.to_sql_str_list(
1915                db_model=self, force_sql=True, sql_format_options=sql_format_options
1916            )
1917        if sql_format_options.annotate:
1918            model_descr = re.sub(r"\s+", " ", str(self))
1919            sql_str_list = [
1920                f"-- data_algebra SQL https://github.com/WinVector/data_algebra",
1921                f"--  dialect: {model_descr} {data_algebra.__version__}",
1922                f"--       string quote: {self.string_quote}",
1923                f"--   identifier quote: {self.identifier_quote}",
1924            ] + sql_str_list
1925        sql_str_list = [v.rstrip() for v in sql_str_list]
1926        sql_str_list = [v for v in sql_str_list if len(v) > 0]
1927        return "\n".join(sql_str_list) + "\n"

1929    def row_recs_to_blocks_query_str_list_pair(
1930        self, record_spec
1931    ) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
1932        """
1933        Convert row recs to blocks transformation into structures to help with SQL conversion.
1934        """
1935        control_value_cols = [
1936            c
1937            for c in record_spec.control_table.columns
1938            if c not in record_spec.control_table_keys
1939        ]
1940        control_cols = [
1941            "a." + self.quote_identifier(c) for c in record_spec.record_keys
1942        ] + [
1943            "b." + self.quote_identifier(key_col)
1944            for key_col in record_spec.control_table_keys
1945        ]
1946        col_stmts = []
1947        for c in record_spec.record_keys:
1948            col_stmts.append(
1949                " a." + self.quote_identifier(c) + " AS " + self.quote_identifier(c)
1950            )
1951        for key_col in record_spec.control_table_keys:
1952            col_stmts.append(
1953                " b."
1954                + self.quote_identifier(key_col)
1955                + " AS "
1956                + self.quote_identifier(key_col)
1957            )
1958        seen = set()
1959        for result_col in control_value_cols:
1960            if result_col in seen:
1961                continue
1962            seen.add(result_col)
1963            cstmt = " CASE "
1964            col = record_spec.control_table[result_col]
1965            isnull = col.isnull()
1966            for i in range(len(col)):
1967                if not (isnull[i]):
1968                    source_col = col[i]
1969                    col_sql = (
1970                        "  WHEN CAST(b."
1971                        + self.quote_identifier(result_col)
1972                        + " AS "
1973                        + self.string_type
1974                        + ") = "
1975                        + self.quote_string(str(source_col))
1976                        + " THEN a."
1977                        + self.quote_identifier(source_col)
1978                        + " "
1979                    )
1980                    cstmt = cstmt + col_sql
1981            cstmt = cstmt + " ELSE NULL END AS " + self.quote_identifier(result_col)
1982            col_stmts.append(cstmt)
1983        ctab_sql = self.table_values_to_sql_str_list(record_spec.control_table)
1984        sql_prefix = _list_join_expecting_list(",", col_stmts) + [
1985            "FROM ( SELECT * FROM "
1986        ]
1987        sql_suffix = (
1988            [" ) a"]
1989            + ["CROSS JOIN ("]
1990            + _list_join_expecting_list("", ctab_sql)
1991            + [" ) b"]
1992            + [" ORDER BY"]  # order by not required, but nice to have
1993            + _list_join_expecting_list(", ", control_cols)
1994        )
1995        return sql_prefix, sql_suffix

1997    # noinspection PyUnusedLocal
1998    def blocks_to_row_recs_query_str_list_pair(
1999        self, record_spec
2000    ) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
2001        """
2002        Convert blocks to row recs transform into structures to help with SQL translation.
2003        """
2004        assert record_spec.control_table.shape[0] >= 1
2005        col_stmts = []
2006        for c in record_spec.record_keys:
2007            col_stmts.append(
2008                " " + self.quote_identifier(c) + " AS " + self.quote_identifier(c)
2009            )
2010        if record_spec.control_table.shape[0] == 1:
2011            # special case with one row control table (rowrec)
2012            for cc in record_spec.control_table.columns:
2013                if cc not in record_spec.control_table_keys:
2014                    cc0 = record_spec.control_table[cc][0]
2015                    col_stmts.append(
2016                        " "
2017                        + self.quote_identifier(cc)
2018                        + " AS "
2019                        + self.quote_identifier(cc0)
2020                    )
2021            sql_prefix = _list_join_expecting_list(",", col_stmts) + [
2022                "FROM ( SELECT * FROM "
2023            ]
2024            sql_suffix = [" ) a"]
2025            return sql_prefix, sql_suffix
2026        control_value_cols = [
2027            c
2028            for c in record_spec.control_table.columns
2029            if c not in record_spec.control_table_keys
2030        ]
2031        control_cols = [self.quote_identifier(c) for c in record_spec.record_keys]
2032        seen = set()
2033        for i in range(record_spec.control_table.shape[0]):
2034            for vc in control_value_cols:
2035                col = record_spec.control_table[vc]
2036                isnull = col.isnull()
2037                if col[i] not in seen and not isnull[i]:
2038                    seen.add(col[i])
2039                    clauses = []
2040                    for cc in record_spec.control_table_keys:
2041                        clauses.append(
2042                            " ( CAST("
2043                            + self.quote_identifier(cc)
2044                            + " AS "
2045                            + self.string_type
2046                            + ") = "
2047                            + self.quote_string(str(record_spec.control_table[cc][i]))
2048                            + " ) "
2049                        )
2050                    cstmt = (
2051                        " MAX(CASE WHEN "
2052                        + " AND ".join(clauses)
2053                        + " THEN "
2054                        + self.quote_identifier(vc)
2055                        + " ELSE NULL END) AS "
2056                        + self.quote_identifier(col[i])
2057                    )
2058                    col_stmts.append(cstmt)
2059        sql_prefix = _list_join_expecting_list(",", col_stmts) + [
2060            "FROM ( SELECT * FROM "
2061        ]
2062        sql_suffix = (
2063            [" ) a"]
2064            + ["GROUP BY"]
2065            + _list_join_expecting_list(",", control_cols)
2066            + ["ORDER BY "]  # order by not required, but nice to have
2067            + _list_join_expecting_list(",", control_cols)
2068        )
2069        return sql_prefix, sql_suffix

def value_to_sql(self, v) -> str: 
 999    def value_to_sql(self, v) -> str:
1000        """
1001        Convert a value to valid SQL.
1002        """
1003        if v is None:
1004            return "NULL"
1005        if isinstance(v, data_algebra.expr_rep.ListTerm):
1006            return "(" + ", ".join([self.value_to_sql(vi) for vi in v.value]) + ")"
1007        if isinstance(v, data_algebra.expr_rep.Value):
1008            return self.value_to_sql(v.value)
1009        if isinstance(v, str):
1010            return self.quote_string(v)
1011        if isinstance(v, bool):
1012            if v:
1013                return "TRUE"
1014            else:
1015                return "FALSE"
1016        if isinstance(v, float):
1017            if math.isnan(v):
1018                return "NULL"  # Pandas confuses NaN and None, so we use NULL
1019            return str(v)
1020        if isinstance(v, int):
1021            return str(v)
1022        if isinstance(v, list) or isinstance(v, tuple):
1023            return "(" + ", ".join([self.value_to_sql(vi) for vi in v]) + ")"
1024        return str(v)

def expr_to_sql(self, expression, *, want_inline_parens: bool = False) -> str: 
1061    def expr_to_sql(self, expression, *, want_inline_parens: bool = False) -> str:
1062        """
1063        Convert an expression to SQL.
1064        """
1065        if isinstance(expression, str):
1066            return expression
1067        assert isinstance(expression, data_algebra.expr_rep.PreTerm)
1068        if isinstance(expression, data_algebra.expr_rep.Value):
1069            return self.value_to_sql(expression.value)
1070        if isinstance(expression, data_algebra.expr_rep.ColumnReference):
1071            return self.quote_identifier(expression.column_name)
1072        if isinstance(expression, data_algebra.expr_rep.Expression):
1073            op = expression.op
1074            if op in self.op_replacements.keys():
1075                op = self.op_replacements[op]
1076            elif op.lower() in self.op_replacements.keys():
1077                op = self.op_replacements[op.lower()]
1078            elif op.upper() in self.op_replacements.keys():
1079                op = self.op_replacements[op.upper()]
1080            if op in self.sql_formatters.keys():
1081                return self.sql_formatters[op](self, expression)
1082            if op.lower() in self.sql_formatters.keys():
1083                return self.sql_formatters[op.lower()](self, expression)
1084            if op.upper() in self.sql_formatters.keys():
1085                return self.sql_formatters[op.upper()](self, expression)
1086            if (len(expression.args) > 1) and expression.inline:
1087                subs = [
1088                    self.expr_to_sql(ai, want_inline_parens=True)
1089                    for ai in expression.args
1090                ]
1091                res = ""
1092                if want_inline_parens:
1093                    res = res + "("
1094                assert len(subs) > 0
1095                if len(subs) == 1:
1096                    res = op.upper() + subs[0]
1097                else:
1098                    res = res + (" " + op.upper() + " ").join(subs)
1099                if want_inline_parens:
1100                    res = res + ")"
1101                return res
1102            subs = [
1103                self.expr_to_sql(ai, want_inline_parens=False) for ai in expression.args
1104            ]
1105            return op.upper() + "(" + ", ".join(subs) + ")"
1106        if isinstance(expression, data_algebra.expr_rep.ListTerm):
1107            return self.value_to_sql(expression.value)
1108        raise TypeError("unexpected type: " + str(type(expression)))

def extend_to_near_sql( self, extend_node, *, using=None, temp_id_source=None, sql_format_options=None) -> data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL: 
1175    def extend_to_near_sql(
1176        self, extend_node, *, using=None, temp_id_source=None, sql_format_options=None
1177    ) -> data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL:
1178        """
1179        Convert an extend step into NearSQL.
1180        """
1181        if extend_node.node_name != "ExtendNode":
1182            raise TypeError(
1183                "Expected extend_node to be a data_algebra.data_ops.ExtendNode)"
1184            )
1185        if temp_id_source is None:
1186            temp_id_source = [0]
1187        if using is None:
1188            using = OrderedSet(extend_node.column_names)
1189        using = using.union(
1190            extend_node.partition_by, extend_node.order_by, extend_node.reverse
1191        )
1192        subops = OrderedDict()
1193        for (k, op) in extend_node.ops.items():
1194            if k in using:
1195                subops[k] = op
1196        if len(subops) <= 0:
1197            # using was not None is this case as len(extend_node.ops)>0 and all keys are in extend_node.column_names
1198            return extend_node.sources[0].to_near_sql_implementation_(
1199                db_model=self, using=using, temp_id_source=temp_id_source
1200            )
1201        if len(using) < 1:
1202            raise ValueError("must produce at least one column")
1203        missing = using - set(extend_node.column_names)
1204        if len(missing) > 0:
1205            raise KeyError("referred to unknown columns: " + str(missing))
1206        # get set of columns we need from subquery
1207        subusing = extend_node.columns_used_from_sources(using=using)[0]
1208        subsql = extend_node.sources[0].to_near_sql_implementation_(
1209            db_model=self, using=subusing, temp_id_source=temp_id_source
1210        )
1211        window_term = ""
1212        window_vars = set()
1213        if (
1214            extend_node.windowed_situation
1215            or (len(extend_node.partition_by) > 0)
1216            or (len(extend_node.order_by) > 0)
1217        ):
1218            window_term = " OVER ( "
1219            if len(extend_node.partition_by) > 0:
1220                pt = [self.quote_identifier(ci) for ci in extend_node.partition_by]
1221                window_term = window_term + "PARTITION BY " + ", ".join(pt) + " "
1222                window_vars.update(extend_node.partition_by)
1223            if len(extend_node.order_by) > 0:
1224                revs = set(extend_node.reverse)
1225                rt = [
1226                    self.quote_identifier(ci) + (" DESC" if ci in revs else "")
1227                    for ci in extend_node.order_by
1228                ]
1229                window_term = window_term + "ORDER BY " + ", ".join(rt) + " "
1230                window_vars.update(extend_node.order_by)
1231            window_term = window_term + " ) "
1232        terms: Dict[str, Optional[str]] = OrderedDict()
1233        declared_term_dependencies = OrderedDict()
1234        origcols = [k for k in using if k not in subops.keys()]
1235        for k in origcols:
1236            terms[k] = None
1237            declared_term_dependencies[k] = {k}
1238        for (ci, oi) in subops.items():
1239            terms[ci] = self.expr_to_sql(oi) + window_term
1240            cols_used_in_term: Set[str] = set()
1241            oi.get_column_names(cols_used_in_term)
1242            cols_used_in_term.update(window_vars)
1243            declared_term_dependencies[ci] = cols_used_in_term
1244        annotation = str(extend_node.to_python_src_(print_sources=False, indent=-1))
1245        # TODO: see if we can merge with subsql instead of building a new one
1246        if (
1247            self.allow_extend_merges
1248            and isinstance(subsql, data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQLUnaryStep)
1249            and subsql.mergeable
1250            and (subsql.declared_term_dependencies is not None)
1251            and ((subsql.suffix is None) or (len(subsql.suffix) == 0))
1252        ):
1253            # check detailed merge conditions
1254            def non_trivial_terms(*, dep_dict, term_dict):
1255                """pickout non-trivial terms"""
1256                return [
1257                    ki
1258                    for ki, vi in dep_dict.items()
1259                    if (len(vi - {ki}) > 0)
1260                    or (ki not in vi)
1261                    or ((term_dict[ki] is not None) and (term_dict[ki] != ki))
1262                ]
1263
1264            our_non_trivial_terms = non_trivial_terms(
1265                dep_dict=declared_term_dependencies, term_dict=terms
1266            )
1267            our_needs = set().union(
1268                *[declared_term_dependencies[k] for k in our_non_trivial_terms]
1269            )
1270            sub_non_trivial_terms = non_trivial_terms(
1271                dep_dict=subsql.declared_term_dependencies, term_dict=subsql.terms
1272            )
1273            sub_needs = set().union(
1274                *[subsql.declared_term_dependencies[k] for k in sub_non_trivial_terms]
1275            )
1276            contention = set().union(
1277                set(our_non_trivial_terms).intersection(sub_non_trivial_terms),
1278                set(our_non_trivial_terms).intersection(sub_needs),
1279                set(sub_non_trivial_terms).intersection(our_needs),
1280            )
1281            if len(contention) == 0:
1282                # merge our stuff into subsql
1283                assert subsql.terms is not None  # type hint
1284                if subsql.annotation is None:
1285                    subsql.annotation = annotation
1286                else:
1287                    subsql.annotation = subsql.annotation + "." + annotation
1288                for k in our_non_trivial_terms:
1289                    subsql.terms[k] = terms[k]
1290                    subsql.declared_term_dependencies[k] = declared_term_dependencies[k]
1291                we_use = set.union(
1292                    set(terms.keys()), set(declared_term_dependencies.keys())
1293                )
1294                excess_sub_term_keys = set(subsql.terms.keys()) - we_use
1295                for k in excess_sub_term_keys:
1296                    del subsql.terms[k]
1297                excess_sub_declared_keys = (
1298                    set(subsql.declared_term_dependencies.keys()) - we_use
1299                )
1300                for k in excess_sub_declared_keys:
1301                    del subsql.declared_term_dependencies[k]
1302                return subsql
1303        view_name = "extend_" + str(temp_id_source[0])
1304        temp_id_source[0] = temp_id_source[0] + 1
1305        near_sql = data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQLUnaryStep(
1306            terms=terms,
1307            query_name=view_name,
1308            quoted_query_name=self.quote_identifier(view_name),
1309            sub_sql=subsql.to_bound_near_sql(columns=subusing),
1310            annotation=annotation,
1311            mergeable=True,
1312            declared_term_dependencies=declared_term_dependencies,
1313            ops_key=f"extend({extend_node}, {terms.keys()})",
1314        )
1315        return near_sql

def natural_join_to_near_sql( self, join_node, *, using=None, temp_id_source=None, sql_format_options=None, left_is_first=True) -> data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL: 
1661    def natural_join_to_near_sql(
1662        self,
1663        join_node,
1664        *,
1665        using=None,
1666        temp_id_source=None,
1667        sql_format_options=None,
1668        left_is_first=True,
1669    ) -> data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL:
1670        """
1671        Convert natural join into NearSQL.
1672        """
1673        if temp_id_source is None:
1674            temp_id_source = [0]
1675        if using is None:
1676            using = OrderedSet(join_node.column_names)
1677        view_name = f"natural_join_{temp_id_source[0]}"
1678        left_q = f"join_source_left_{temp_id_source[0]}"
1679        right_q = f"join_source_right_{temp_id_source[0]}"
1680        temp_id_source[0] = temp_id_source[0] + 1
1681        using_left, sql_left, using_right, sql_right = self._natural_join_sub_queries(
1682            join_node=join_node, using=using, temp_id_source=temp_id_source
1683        )
1684        left_qqn = self.quote_identifier(left_q)
1685        right_qqn = self.quote_identifier(right_q)
1686        common = using_left.intersection(using_right)
1687        if left_is_first:
1688            terms = self._coalesce_terms(
1689                sub_view_name_first=left_qqn,
1690                sub_view_name_second=right_qqn,
1691                cols=[ci for ci in common if ci in using],
1692            )
1693        else:
1694            terms = self._coalesce_terms(
1695                sub_view_name_first=right_qqn,
1696                sub_view_name_second=left_qqn,
1697                cols=[ci for ci in common if ci in using],
1698            )
1699        for ci in using_left:
1700            if ci not in common:
1701                terms[ci] = None
1702        for ci in using_right:
1703            if ci not in common:
1704                terms[ci] = None
1705        on_terms = []
1706        if len(join_node.on_a) > 0:
1707            on_terms = ["ON " + self.on_start] + self._indent_and_sep_terms(
1708                [
1709                    left_qqn
1710                    + "."
1711                    + self.quote_identifier(c_a)
1712                    + " = "
1713                    + right_qqn
1714                    + "."
1715                    + self.quote_identifier(c_b)
1716                    for c_a, c_b in zip(join_node.on_a, join_node.on_b)
1717                ],
1718                sep=self.on_joiner,
1719                sql_format_options=sql_format_options,
1720            )
1721            if (self.on_end is not None) and (len(self.on_end) > 0):
1722                on_terms = on_terms + [self.on_end]
1723        near_sql = data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQLBinaryStep(
1724            terms=terms,
1725            query_name=view_name,
1726            quoted_query_name=self.quote_identifier(view_name),
1727            sub_sql1=sql_left.to_bound_near_sql(
1728                columns=using_left,
1729                force_sql=False,
1730                public_name=left_q,
1731                public_name_quoted=left_qqn,
1732            ),
1733            joiner=join_node.jointype + " JOIN",
1734            sub_sql2=sql_right.to_bound_near_sql(
1735                columns=using_right,
1736                force_sql=False,

1738                public_name_quoted=right_qqn,
1739            ),

1748    ) -> data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL:
1749        """
1750        Convert concat rows into NearSQL.

def to_sql( self, ops: data_algebra.data_ops.ViewRepresentation, *, sql_format_options: Optional[data_algebra.sql_format_options.SQLFormatOptions] = None) -> str: 
1832    def to_sql(
1833        self,
1834        ops: data_algebra.data_ops.ViewRepresentation,
1835        *,
1836        sql_format_options: Optional[SQLFormatOptions] = None,
1837    ) -> str:
1838        """
1839        Convert ViewRepresentation into SQL string.
1840
1841        :param ops: ViewRepresentation to convert
1842        :param sql_format_options: sql formatting options
1843        :return: sql string
1844        """
1845        assert isinstance(self, DBModel)
1846        assert isinstance(ops, data_algebra.data_ops.ViewRepresentation)
1847        if sql_format_options is None:
1848            sql_format_options = self.default_SQL_format_options
1849        assert isinstance(sql_format_options, SQLFormatOptions)
1850        ops.columns_used()  # for table consistency check/raise
1851        if sql_format_options.warn_on_novel_methods:
1852            non_known = self.non_known_methods(ops)
1853            if len(non_known) > 0:
1854                warnings.warn(
1855                    f"{self} translation using undocumented method context: {non_known}",
1856                    UserWarning,
1857                )
1858        if sql_format_options.warn_on_method_support:
1859            non_rec = self.non_recommended_methods(ops)
1860            if len(non_rec) > 0:
1861                warnings.warn(
1862                    f"{self} translation doesn't fully support method context: {non_rec}",
1863                    UserWarning,
1864                )
1865        # TODO: put common sub-expression control object here and pass into converters
1866        temp_id_source = [0]
1867        near_sql = ops.to_near_sql_implementation_(
1868            db_model=self, using=None, temp_id_source=temp_id_source
1869        )
1870        assert isinstance(near_sql, data_algebra.near_sql.NearSQL)
1871        sql_str_list = None
1872        if sql_format_options.use_with and self.supports_with:
1873            cte_cache: Optional[Dict] = None
1874            if (
1875                sql_format_options.use_cte_elim
1876                and self.supports_with
1877                and self.supports_cte_elim
1878            ):
1879                cte_cache = dict()
1880            sequence = near_sql.to_with_form(cte_cache=cte_cache)
1881            len_sequence = len(sequence.previous_steps)
1882            # can fall back to the non-with path
1883            if len(sequence.previous_steps) >= 1:
1884                sql_sequence: List[str] = []
1885                for i in range(len_sequence):
1886                    nmi = sequence.previous_steps[i][0]  # already quoted
1887                    sqli = sequence.previous_steps[i][1].convert_subsql(
1888                        db_model=self, sql_format_options=sql_format_options
1889                    )
1890                    sql_sequence = (
1891                        sql_sequence
1892                        + [f"{sql_format_options.sql_indent}{nmi} AS ("]
1893                        + [
1894                            sql_format_options.sql_indent
1895                            + sql_format_options.sql_indent
1896                            + s
1897                            for s in sqli
1898                        ]
1899                    )
1900                    if i < (len_sequence - 1):
1901                        sql_sequence = sql_sequence + [
1902                            sql_format_options.sql_indent + ") ,"
1903                        ]
1904                    else:
1905                        sql_sequence = sql_sequence + [
1906                            sql_format_options.sql_indent + ")"
1907                        ]
1908                sql_last = sequence.last_step.to_sql_str_list(
1909                    db_model=self, force_sql=True, sql_format_options=sql_format_options
1910                )
1911                sql_str_list = ["WITH"] + sql_sequence + sql_last
1912        if sql_str_list is None:
1913            # non-with path
1914            sql_str_list = near_sql.to_sql_str_list(
1915                db_model=self, force_sql=True, sql_format_options=sql_format_options
1916            )
1917        if sql_format_options.annotate:
1918            model_descr = re.sub(r"\s+", " ", str(self))
1919            sql_str_list = [
1920                f"-- data_algebra SQL https://github.com/WinVector/data_algebra",
1921                f"--  dialect: {model_descr} {data_algebra.__version__}",
1922                f"--       string quote: {self.string_quote}",
1923                f"--   identifier quote: {self.identifier_quote}",
1924            ] + sql_str_list
1925        sql_str_list = [v.rstrip() for v in sql_str_list]
1926        sql_str_list = [v for v in sql_str_list if len(v) > 0]
1927        return "\n".join(sql_str_list) + "\n"

1954                + self.quote_identifier(key_col)
1955                + " AS "
1956                + self.quote_identifier(key_col)
1957            )
1958        seen = set()
1959        for result_col in control_value_cols:
1960            if result_col in seen:
1961                continue
1962            seen.add(result_col)
1963            cstmt = " CASE "
1964            col = record_spec.control_table[result_col]
1965            isnull = col.isnull()
1966            for i in range(len(col)):
1967                if not (isnull[i]):
1968                    source_col = col[i]
1969                    col_sql = (
1970                        "  WHEN CAST(b."
1971                        + self.quote_identifier(result_col)
1972                        + " AS "
1973                        + self.string_type
1974                        + ") = "
1975                        + self.quote_string(str(source_col))
1976                        + " THEN a."
1977                        + self.quote_identifier(source_col)
1978                        + " "
1979                    )
1980                    cstmt = cstmt + col_sql
1981            cstmt = cstmt + " ELSE NULL END AS " + self.quote_identifier(result_col)
1982            col_stmts.append(cstmt)
1983        ctab_sql = self.table_values_to_sql_str_list(record_spec.control_table)
1984        sql_prefix = _list_join_expecting_list(",", col_stmts) + [
1985            "FROM ( SELECT * FROM "
1986        ]
1987        sql_suffix = (
1988            [" ) a"]
1989            + ["CROSS JOIN ("]
1990            + _list_join_expecting_list("", ctab_sql)
1991            + [" ) b"]
1992            + [" ORDER BY"]  # order by not required, but nice to have
1993            + _list_join_expecting_list(", ", control_cols)
1994        )
1995        return sql_prefix, sql_suffix

def blocks_to_row_recs_query_str_list_pair(self, record_spec) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]: 
1998    def blocks_to_row_recs_query_str_list_pair(
1999        self, record_spec
2000    ) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
2001        """
2002        Convert blocks to row recs transform into structures to help with SQL translation.
2003        """
2004        assert record_spec.control_table.shape[0] >= 1
2005        col_stmts = []
2006        for c in record_spec.record_keys:
2007            col_stmts.append(
2008                " " + self.quote_identifier(c) + " AS " + self.quote_identifier(c)
2009            )
2010        if record_spec.control_table.shape[0] == 1:
2011            # special case with one row control table (rowrec)
2012            for cc in record_spec.control_table.columns:
2013                if cc not in record_spec.control_table_keys:
2014                    cc0 = record_spec.control_table[cc][0]
2015                    col_stmts.append(
2016                        " "
2017                        + self.quote_identifier(cc)
2018                        + " AS "
2019                        + self.quote_identifier(cc0)
2020                    )
2021            sql_prefix = _list_join_expecting_list(",", col_stmts) + [
2022                "FROM ( SELECT * FROM "
2023            ]
2024            sql_suffix = [" ) a"]
2025            return sql_prefix, sql_suffix
2026        control_value_cols = [
2027            c
2028            for c in record_spec.control_table.columns
2029            if c not in record_spec.control_table_keys
2030        ]
2031        control_cols = [self.quote_identifier(c) for c in record_spec.record_keys]
2032        seen = set()
2033        for i in range(record_spec.control_table.shape[0]):
2034            for vc in control_value_cols:
2035                col = record_spec.control_table[vc]
2036                isnull = col.isnull()
2037                if col[i] not in seen and not isnull[i]:
2038                    seen.add(col[i])
2039                    clauses = []
2040                    for cc in record_spec.control_table_keys:
2041                        clauses.append(
2042                            " ( CAST("
2043                            + self.quote_identifier(cc)
2044                            + " AS "
2045                            + self.string_type
2046                            + ") = "
2047                            + self.quote_string(str(record_spec.control_table[cc][i]))
2048                            + " ) "
2049                        )
2050                    cstmt = (
2051                        " MAX(CASE WHEN "
2052                        + " AND ".join(clauses)
2053                        + " THEN "
2054                        + self.quote_identifier(vc)
2055                        + " ELSE NULL END) AS "
2056                        + self.quote_identifier(col[i])
2057                    )
2058                    col_stmts.append(cstmt)
2059        sql_prefix = _list_join_expecting_list(",", col_stmts) + [
2060            "FROM ( SELECT * FROM "
2061        ]
2062        sql_suffix = (
2063            [" ) a"]
2064            + ["GROUP BY"]
2065            + _list_join_expecting_list(",", control_cols)
2066            + ["ORDER BY "]  # order by not required, but nice to have
2067            + _list_join_expecting_list(",", control_cols)
2068        )
2069        return sql_prefix, sql_suffix
